{"type":"message","id":"2e83cfa5","parentId":"b7dd9796","timestamp":"2026-03-20T09:33:49.776Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Sender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"openclaw-tui (gateway-client)\",\n  \"id\": \"gateway-client\",\n  \"name\": \"openclaw-tui\",\n  \"username\": \"openclaw-tui\"\n}\n```\n\n[Fri 2026-03-20 11:33 GMT+2] I restarted it myself. I have a few question. Firstly, in the openclaw.json file under models, there is a parameter called context window now set at 60000 and a max tokens which is still set at 128000. What is the difference between these two?"}],"timestamp":1773999229773}}
{"type":"message","id":"cd553c8a","parentId":"2e83cfa5","timestamp":"2026-03-20T09:33:52.524Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"**contextWindow** = total tokens the model can handle in a single request (input + output combined). At 60k, your prompt + response can't exceed 60k tokens.\n\n**maxTokens** = limit on output alone (how long the response can be). Independent of input.\n\nSo with your current settings:\n- Input + output ≤ 60,000 tokens\n- But output capped at 128,000 tokens\n\nThe maxTokens is currently meaningless since it's capped by contextWindow anyway. Want me to lower that too?"}],"stopReason":"stop","api":"ollama","provider":"ollama","model":"minimax-m2.5:cloud","usage":{"input":23341,"output":133,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":23474,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"timestamp":1773999232519}}
