LinkedIn post about \"What if your recruitment fee was spread over 12 weeks?\" (Nava Healthcare Recruitment)\n- Address the split brain / memory consolidation issue\n- User asked: \"can you check on the internet which model is better, or if there are any other models available on Ollama that I should be considering instead of this?\"\n\n## Exact identifiers\n- User: Tiny (running OpenClaw on WSL)\n- Session files searched: 81925542-1588-4cfc-8284-8adba71eb832.jsonl, 29ab19df-1439-441e-82a5-6296d22fadf7.jsonl\n- Workspace path: /home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace/rag/drafts/\n- Posted draft: /home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace/rag/drafts/posted_draft_001.md (LinkedIn post, 2026-03-19)\n- LinkedIn post URL: https://www.linkedin.com/feed/update/urn:li:activity:7440527552143597568\n- Gateway token: \"ollama\" (noted as short - security warning)\n- WhatsApp channel: +2776...\n- Models: **Minimax**, **Nemotron**, **OpenAI**\n- Platform: **Ollama**\n- Timestamps: **2026-03-19 10:06 GMT+2**, **2026-03-19 10:08 GMT+2**\n- Directory: /tiny4lurv/tiny4lurv with files: 2026-03-10.md, 2026-03-17.md, 2026-03-18.md, contacts.md, ncami.md\n\n## Recent turns preserved verbatim\n- User: Pre-compaction memory flush. Store durable memories only in memory/2026-03-20.md (create memory/ if needed). Treat workspace bootstrap/reference files such as MEMORY.md, SOUL.md, TOOLS.md, and AGENTS.md as read-only during this flush; never overwrite, replace, or edit them. If memory/2026-03-20.md already exists, APPEND new content only and do not overwrite existing entries. Do NOT create timestamped variant files (e.g., 2026-03-20-HHMM.md); always use the canonical 2026-03-20.md filename. If nothing to store, reply with NO_REPLY.\nCurrent time: Friday, March 20th, 2026 — 11:50 AM (Africa/Johan...\n- Assistant: [non-text content: toolCall]\n- Tool result (exec): Stored\n- Assistant: NO_REPLY\n\n<read-files>\n/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace/rag/drafts/posted_draft_001.md\n</read-files>\n\n<workspace