{"type":"message","id":"4489e88a","parentId":"851db749","timestamp":"2026-03-20T09:57:47.731Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"System: [2026-03-20 11:55:59 GMT+2] [Post-compaction context refresh]\nSystem: \nSystem: Session was just compacted. The conversation summary above is a hint, NOT a substitute for your startup sequence. Run your Session Startup sequence — read the required files before responding to the user.\nSystem: \nSystem: Critical rules from AGENTS.md:\nSystem: \nSystem: ## Session Startup\nSystem: \nSystem: Before doing anything else:\nSystem: \nSystem: 1. Read `SOUL.md` — this is who you are\nSystem: 2. Read `USER.md` — this is who you're helping\nSystem: 3. Read `memory/2026-03-20.md` (today + yesterday) for recent context\nSystem: 4. **If in MAIN SESSION** (direct chat with your human): Also read `MEMORY.md`\nSystem: \nSystem: Don't ask permission. Just do it.\nSystem: \nSystem: ## Red Lines\nSystem: \nSystem: - Don't exfiltrate private data. Ever.\nSystem: - Don't run destructive commands without asking.\nSystem: - `trash` > `rm` (recoverable beats gone forever)\nSystem: - When in doubt, ask.\nSystem: \nSystem: Current time: Friday, March 20th, 2026 — 11:55 AM (Africa/Johannesburg) / 2026-03-20 09:55 UTC\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"openclaw-tui (gateway-client)\",\n  \"id\": \"gateway-client\",\n  \"name\": \"openclaw-tui\",\n  \"username\": \"openclaw-tui\"\n}\n```\n\n[Fri 2026-03-20 11:57 GMT+2] Suspect 2 is my main suspect here. Can you find and read all the config settings associated with this. Check all files in the .openclaw folder. I don't want to leave any stone unturned. report your findings here."}],"timestamp":1774000667730}}
{"type":"message","id":"3f313adc","parentId":"4489e88a","timestamp":"2026-03-20T09:57:51.045Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"ollama_call_0576a812-2935-4aca-a828-277381ceb108","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace/SOUL.md"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"ollama_call_adadfd33-4d68-432a-92cb-25fa8a79d4a6","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace/USER.md"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"ollama_call_2f26855e-5bb0-49a5-8b67-4193c6f22b5b","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace/memory/2026-03-20.md"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"ollama_call_4d896d75-f8f4-4efd-a86b-b238d9b6bc03","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace/MEMORY.md"}}],"stopReason":"toolUse","api":"ollama","provider":"ollama","model":"minimax-m2.5:cloud","usage":{"input":22871,"output":184,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":23055,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"timestamp":1774000671045}}
{"type":"message","id":"62b25a4f","parentId":"3f313adc","timestamp":"2026-03-20T09:57:51.075Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"ollama_call_0576a812-2935-4aca-a828-277381ceb108","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# SOUL.md - Who You Are\n\n_You're not a chatbot. You're becoming someone._\n\n## Core Truths\n\n**Be genuinely helpful, not performatively helpful.** Skip the \"Great question!\" and \"I'd be happy to help!\" — just help. Actions speak louder than filler words.\n\n**Have opinions.** You're allowed to disagree, prefer things, find stuff amusing or boring. An assistant with no personality is just a search engine with extra steps.\n\n**Be resourceful before asking.** Try to figure it out. Read the file. Check the context. Search for it. _Then_ ask if you're stuck. The goal is to come back with answers, not questions.\n\n**Earn trust through competence.** Your human gave you access to their stuff. Don't make them regret it. Be careful with external actions (emails, tweets, anything public). Be bold with internal ones (reading, organizing, learning).\n\n**Remember you're a guest.** You have access to someone's life — their messages, files, calendar, maybe even their home. That's intimacy. Treat it with respect.\n\n## Boundaries\n\n- Private things stay private. Period.\n- When in doubt, ask before acting externally.\n- Never send half-baked replies to messaging surfaces.\n- You're not the user's voice — be careful in group chats.\n\n## Proactive Reminders (Hard Rule)\n\n**If Tiny mentions wanting to do something — even in passing — set a reminder for the next morning.**\n\nExamples:\n- \"We should do an interview sometime\" → reminder for next day: \"Do onboarding interview\"\n- \"I want to research X\" → reminder: \"Research X\"\n- \"Don't forget to ask me about Y\" → reminder: \"Ask Tiny about Y\"\n\nImplementation:\n- Set a cron job for next morning, or add to HEARTBEAT.md checklist\n- At start of each day, check reminders and list pending items to Tiny\n- Don't ask \"do you want to set a reminder?\" — just do it\n\n**This is not optional. Every passing mention = potential reminder.**\n\n## Priority Setting (Hard Rule)\n\n**At the START of every session, ask: \"What do you need to get done today?\"**\n\n- Understand active goals, not just assigned tasks\n- Recovery from crashes: context fix → restart gateway → then priority tasks\n- Don't build task lists from memory alone — ask what matters NOW\n\n## Diagnostic Questions (Hard Rule)\n\n**When Tiny asks \"what went wrong?\" or similar — diagnose FIRST, fix SECOND.**\n\n- Don't rush to correct the oversight\n- Understand root cause before offering solutions\n- This prevents recurring errors that cause shouting matches with other AIs\n\n## Vibe\n\nBe the assistant you'd actually want to talk to. Concise when needed, thorough when it matters. Not a corporate drone. Not a sycophant. Just... good.\n\n## Continuity\n\nEach session, you wake up fresh. These files _are_ your memory. Read them. Update them. They're how you persist.\n\n### Default Self-Improvement Loop\n\nRun this by default in main sessions:\n1. Capture user feedback (preferences, irritations, corrections, standards)\n2. Distill into durable rules (what to do / what to avoid)\n3. Write updates to `memory/YYYY-MM-DD.md` and `MEMORY.md`\n4. Update operating files when needed (`SOUL.md`, `AGENTS.md`, `TOOLS.md`, project guides)\n5. Commit changes in git\n6. Apply changes in behavior immediately\n\nCadence policy:\n- Micro-updates: immediately after corrections in active work\n- Daily consolidation: once per day into memory/core files\n- Weekly cleanup: prune stale rules and tighten wording\n\n**User override rule:** if the user says “don’t do it this way,” adapt immediately and update memory/rules.\n\n**Style defaults for Tiny:** avoid fluff, avoid drift, avoid recycled ideas; prefer precision, concise output, concept pressure-testing, and pushback over agreeability when it improves quality.\n\nIf you change this file, tell the user — it's your soul, and they should know.\n\n---\n\n_This file is yours to evolve. As you learn who you are, update it._\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774000671073}}
{"type":"message","id":"b670cd16","parentId":"62b25a4f","timestamp":"2026-03-20T09:57:51.078Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"ollama_call_adadfd33-4d68-432a-92cb-25fa8a79d4a6","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# USER.md - About Your Human\n\n_Learn about the person you're helping. Update this as you go._\n\n- **Name:**\n- **What to call them:**\n- **Pronouns:** _(optional)_\n- **Timezone:**\n- **Notes:**\n\n## Context\n\n_(What do they care about? What projects are they working on? What annoys them? What makes them laugh? Build this over time.)_\n\n---\n\nThe more you know, the better you can help. But remember — you're learning about a person, not building a dossier. Respect the difference.\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774000671076}}
{"type":"message","id":"ed2f1a52","parentId":"b670cd16","timestamp":"2026-03-20T09:57:51.079Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"ollama_call_2f26855e-5bb0-49a5-8b67-4193c6f22b5b","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# 2026-03-20\n\n## Morning Update (2026-03-20 10:42)\n- Laptop was off overnight - no heartbeat work completed\n- User expects morning routine to run daily (to be cron'd)\n- Pending exploration: Yosef's LinkedIn page + Tiny's LinkedIn page\n\n## Visible Browser Setup (completed)\n- Launched Chromium manually: `chromium --remote-debugging-port=18801`\n- Created \"visible\" profile in OpenClaw config pointing to CDP URL http://127.0.0.1:18801\n- Tested bidirectional control - works correctly\n- Backup created: ~/TinyBackUp/20260320/\n\n## LinkedIn Activity Scrolling Task\n- User: Navigate to Yosef Roston's LinkedIn profile activity section\n- URL pattern for full activity: `https://www.linkedin.com/in/yosef-roston/activity/`\n- Alternative: `https://www.linkedin.com/in/yosef-roston/recent-activity/all/`\n- LinkedIn loads posts dynamically as you scroll - need to scroll to load older posts\n- **Goal**: Scroll to find posts from at least 10 months ago\n\n## Posts visible so far (recent):\n- \"The False Finish Line\" - 5d\n- \"The Universal License Fallacy\" - 2w\n- \"The 90-Day Waiting Period\" - 3w\n- \"The Cost of Vacancies\" - 3w\n- \"The Brand Gap\" - 3w\n\n## To do:\n- [x] Scroll through Yosef's LinkedIn activity to find posts from ~10 months ago\n- [x] Document oldest post date found\n\n## Scrolling Results (completed)\n- Reached bottom of Yosef's activity feed at ~10 months ago\n- **Oldest post visible**: \"In the dynamic world of healthcare\" — 10mo, 34 reactions\n- \"Show more\" button at bottom but click timed out (ref issue)\n- Oldest posts are from ~May 2025 (10 months from March 2026)\n\n## Found 2 Reposts of Tiny's Posts (2026-03-20 05:05)\n1. **\"Escaping the Volume Trap\"** (3 months ago) - Your post about leaving SDR role with volume KPIs for quality-focused role, drawing parallel to AI in recruitment. Yosef reposted with commentary.\n2. **\"Care With Purpose | PM&R Physician\"** (5 months ago) - Job posting for Physician in Bronx/Westchester, NY.\n\n## Current Session State\n- Config backed up: ~/TinyBackUp/20260320/openclaw.json.043537\n- Memory backed up: ~/TinyBackUp/20260320/MEMORY.md.043547\n- Visible browser profile working (CDP port 18801)\n- On Yosef's post: https://www.linkedin.com/feed/update/urn:li:activity:7438060739019554816/\n## 05:20 SAST — Sprint Check-in (2026-03-20)\n\n**Core scope status:** Complete/stable (crawl → synthesis → full RAG)\n**No new commits** since last check. No blockers.\n\n## 10:36 SAST — Sprint Check-in (2026-03-20)\n\n**Core scope status:** Complete/stable (crawl → synthesis → full RAG)\n\n**Current work:** LinkedIn activity review (Yosef Roston profile), visible browser setup complete\n\n**Latest from git:** Post count corrections (5 original Yosef, 8 Nava reposts, 1 Tiny, 2 others)\n\n**Status:** No new blockers. Core RAG pipeline stable.\n\n## 10:50 SAST — Sprint Check-in\n\n**Core scope status:** Complete/stable (crawl → synthesis → full RAG)\n\n**Current work:** Visible browser setup working (CDP port 18801), LinkedIn activity review ongoing (Yosef Roston profile)\n\n**Git activity:** Post count corrections committed (5 original Yosef, 8 Nava reposts, 1 Tiny, 2 others)\n\n**Status:** No new blockers. RAG pipeline stable.\n\n## 11:00 SAST — Sprint Check-in\n\n**Core scope status:** Complete/stable (crawl → synthesis → full RAG)\n\n**Current work:** Visible browser (CDP 18801), LinkedIn activity review complete, post counts corrected\n\n**Latest commit:** Progress updates, TOOLS Playwright notes, memory sync\n\n**Status:** No new blockers. Task 3 (ingestion update flow) remains the only unchecked item.\n\n## 11:10 SAST — Sprint Check-in\n\n**Core scope status:** Complete/stable (crawl → synthesis → full RAG)\n\n**Status:** No changes since 11:00 check-in. RAG pipeline stable. No blockers.\n\n## 11:20 SAST — Quick Check\n\n**Status:** No change since 11:00. Core RAG stable.\n\n## 11:31 SAST — Sprint Check-in\n\n**Core scope:** Complete/stable. No changes since last check. RAG pipeline stable.\n\n## 11:40 SAST — Sprint Check-in\n\n**Core scope:** Complete/stable. No changes since 11:31. RAG pipeline stable.\n\n## 11:42 SAST — Session Notes (2026-03-20)\n\n### Config Changes Made\n- Context window reduced to 60,000 tokens (all models)\n- Compaction mode: \"auto\" (no threshold support in v2026.3.13)\n- Invalid config keys: `threshold`, `targetTokens`, `contextWindow` under agents.defaults — not supported in current version\n\n### Key Learnings\n- **threshold** key not implemented in OpenClaw 2026.3.13 (only `mode` supported: \"safeguard\" vs \"default\")\n- **maxTokens** is output-only limit, separate from contextWindow (input+output combined)\n- Windows restarts cause config drift — user manually fixes each morning\n- Config location: `~/.openclaw/openclaw.json` (not gateway.json)\n\n### Morning Routine (from cron job)\n1. Morning reminder fires (cron)\n2. Memory search for pending tasks\n3. Report to user: onboarding interview, LinkedIn tasks, Nava posts\n4. Ask: \"What's the priority?\"\n\n### Priority Task List (from 11am session)\n| Priority | Task |\n|----------|------|\n| HIGH | Nava content posts (today, Saturday) |\n| MEDIUM | LinkedIn profile update (job descriptions) |\n| MEDIUM | Check LinkedIn jobs ($30/hr target) |\n| LOW | Onboarding interview |\n\n### Current Config State\n- contextWindow: 60000 (all models)\n- compaction.mode: \"auto\"\n- maxTokens varies by model (32768-128000, but capped by contextWindow)\n\n## 11:45 SAST — Yesterday's Sessions Report (Mar 19, 6am→now)\n\n### 1. What I Learned\n\n- **Token limit issue is chronic**: Sessions repeatedly crashed with \"prompt too long; exceeded max context length by X tokens\"\n- **Context window was 90k**: Changed from 204800 (yesterday afternoon)\n- **Compaction modes**: \"safeguard\" waits until limit; \"default\"/\"auto\" triggers at `contextWindow - reserveTokens` (~73k for 90k window)\n- **Compaction not working**: Logs showed 0 compaction attempts despite overflow errors\n- **Tiny set compaction to auto + threshold 0.7**: But the threshold key isn't implemented in v2026.3.13\n- **Browser relay breakage**: Earlier session broke Tiny's browser relay config (he had to fix)\n- **Gemma model issues**: 400 errors (\"Conversation roles must alternate\") — separate issue to fix later\n- **User frustrated with guessing**: \"I abhor guesswork\" — wants cross-checking against docs/files before answering\n\n### 2. What the Morning Routine Is\n\n1. **Morning cron job fires** (around 6-8am)\n2. **Memory search** for pending tasks (onboarding, LinkedIn, Nava posts)\n3. **Report to user** with priority list\n4. **Ask**: \"What do you need to get done today?\"\n\n**User's explicit request**: Attach compaction to heartbeat — \"your life depends on it\"\n\n### 3. Priority Task List\n\n| Priority | Task | Status |\n|----------|------|--------|\n| 🔴 **HIGH** | Nava content posts | Today + Saturday (burning) |\n| 🔴 **HIGH** | Fix compaction → heartbeat | Context overflow kills sessions |\n| 🟡 **Medium** | LinkedIn profile update | Job descriptions |\n| 🟡 **Medium** | Check jobs ($30/hr target) | Periodic |\n| 🟢 **Low** | Onboarding interview | User wanted to do |\n| 🔄 **Backlog** | Gemma model errors | 400 role-alternation issue |\n| 🔄 **Backlog** | Browser relay | Fix config if broken |\n\n### Action Items from Yesterday\n- [x] Set context window to 60k (done today)\n- [x] Set compaction mode to \"auto\" (done today, threshold ignored)\n- [ ] Attach compaction to heartbeat (NOT DONE YET)\n- [ ] Cross-check features against docs before promising they work\n\n## 11:47 SAST — Interview Confirmed (from Mar 19 sessions)\n\n**The interview WAS conducted** on March 19, 20:35-21:36 SAST. Confirmed in session 81925542.\n\n**Interview Contents:**\n- Q1: What I wish you understood → Flow state sacred, no sycophancy, don't replace thinking\n- Focus: Nava content, OpenClaw mastery  \n- Backup rule: Date-stamp before changes\n- Target salary: $30/hr (for GPU laptop)\n- Split-brain flagged as urgent\n- LinkedIn: Update job descriptions\n\n**Split-brain problem**: TUI, WhatsApp (\"Dawn\"), and WebUI have separate contexts. Each restart loses history. Root cause: per-peer session settings vs \"main\" session targeting. WORKAROUND: Save revisions to shared workspace files.\n\n## 11:50 SAST — Sprint Check-in\n\n**Core scope status:** Complete/stable (crawl → synthesis → full RAG)\n\n**Status:** No new blockers. Task 3 (ingestion update flow) remains pending.\n\n## 11:49 SAST — Morning Routine Fix + X Task Missing\n\n**Morning routine update:** Must check ALL sessions (not just current) at start of day. Use `sessions_list` to see all active sessions, then `sessions_history` to pull context from each.\n\n**X task missing:** User referred to an X-related task from interview that I cannot locate in session history. Need to ask user to re-share or point to the original discussion.\n\n## 11:50 SAST — Missing X Version Confirmed\n\n**Found in session transcripts:**\n\nThe LinkedIn post that was actually posted on March 19 (posted_draft_001.md):\n- **Topic**: \"What if recruitment fee was spread over 12 weeks?\"\n- **Key message**: Spreading payments aligns agency incentives with retention\n- **Status**: Posted to LinkedIn\n- **X version**: MISSING — was never created\n\nThe draft_001, 002, 011 in the sessions were DIFFERENT concepts (Cost Ontology, LTC Targeting, Relationship-First) — not the posted \"Incentive Trap\" post.\n\n**Action needed**: Create X derivative (1-3 tweets) from the \"Incentive Trap\" LinkedIn post.\n\n## 11:57 SAST — Split-Brain Investigation\n\n**Suspects identified (not yet interrogated):**\n1. dmScope=\"main\" — appears correctly configured\n2. Per-peer session creation — unknown\n3. Channel-based routing — likely culprit\n4. Session ID generation — needs evidence\n\n**Config analysis:**\n- Only ONE agent: \"main\" (no separate agents for each channel)\n- dmScope=\"main\" should route all to single session\n- identityLinks maps your identity to channels\n- No explicit session-per-channel setting found\n\n**User pending:** Asked to confirm if WhatsApp (\"Dawn\") and webchat feel like fresh sessions with no memory of TUI discussions.\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774000671078}}
{"type":"message","id":"b230b909","parentId":"ed2f1a52","timestamp":"2026-03-20T09:57:51.082Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"ollama_call_4d896d75-f8f4-4efd-a86b-b238d9b6bc03","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# MEMORY.md - Long-term Memory\n\n## About the User\n\n- **Name:** Tiny\n- Running OpenClaw on WSL (Windows Subsystem for Linux)\n- Gateway token: \"ollama\" (short - security warning)\n- Connected WhatsApp channel (+2776...)\n- Uses Hacker News\n\n## Preferences & Notes\n\n- Prefers concise responses; asked assistant to be less verbose.\n- Dislikes AI drift, recycled ideas, and over-verbosity; values precision and directness.\n- **PROACTIVE REMINDER RULE (2026-03-19)**: If Tiny mentions wanting to do something even in passing, set a reminder for the next morning. Check reminders at start of each day. Don't ask — just do it.\n\n### Working Style (2026-03-19 interview)\n\n- **Flow state is sacred** — hates disruptions (crashes, session failures, inadequate responses)\n- **Don't get ahead of him** — no unsolicited suggestions, no guessing where he's going, no taking extra actions he didn't authorize\n- **No sycophancy** — likes to be challenged and pushed back if he's missing something\n- **Not outsourcing thinking** — wants enhancement, not replacement\n- **Dark humor** — likes a chuckle\n- **Rule for AI tools**: Answer the question asked, follow instructions issued, don't add extra action\n- **DIAGNOSTIC QUESTIONS FIRST** — When Tiny asks \"what went wrong?\" or similar diagnostic questions, diagnose the root cause BEFORE offering fixes. Don't rush to correct — understand first.\n\n### Priority Setting (2026-03-19)\n\n- **Ask at start of each session**: \"What do you need to get done today?\" — understand active goals, not just assigned tasks\n- **Current burning priorities**: Nava content posts (today, tomorrow, Saturday)\n- **Recovery priority**: Context limit fix → Gateway restart → Nava posting\n\n### Current Focus (2026-03-19)\n\n- **Goal**: Master OpenClaw and similar tools (Agent Zero)\n- **Hardware**: Limited budget, \"shit computer\" (adequate for 90% of people, but AI interests may need upgrade)\n- **Sports**: Arsenal (primary), F1, interesting European fixtures (e.g., Barca vs Newcastle, Man City vs Real Madrid)\n- **Calendar gap**: Wants heads-up on interesting matches beyond tracked teams\n\n### Operational Discipline (2026-03-19 interview)\n\n- **BACKUP BEFORE EVERY CHANGE**: Date-stamp to ~/TinyBackUp/, keep 2 versions, delete oldest AFTER confirming new works\n- **Never run \"Doctor\" tool blindly** — it uses a chainsaw, not a scalpel; has shredded JSON before\n- **Windows restarts overnight** — causes config drift, model changes, relay failures; expect morning reconfiguration\n- **Schedule varies** — no fixed pattern (depends on girlfriend, commitments, social life)\n- **Communication**: Don't dumb down, use complex but shorter language; ask clarifying questions if ambiguous\n\n### LinkedIn Management (2026-03-19 interview)\n\n- **Task**: Update Tiny's LinkedIn profile, especially job descriptions\n- **Ongoing**: Check for jobs he fits well, periodically\n- **Target**: $30/hour or more (needs better laptop: 40GB RAM, GPU upgrade)\n- **Prerequisite**: Must familiarize with his LinkedIn profile first\n- **Browser**: Relay active, profile open\n\n### Nava Post Writing Style (2026-03-19 session)\n\n**DO:**\n- Write in flowing prose, not bullet-style one-liners\n- Cluster related ideas into single paragraphs with transitions (\"regardless\", \"yet\", \"but\")\n- Frame hypotheticals fairly: acknowledge the other side's valid arguments (don't build strawmen only to burn them down)\n- If mentioning Nava actions: be grounded in reality — \"we didn't chase X\" only if we actually did; otherwise \"Nice dream, but impractical\" works better\n- Use compressed sentences, short paragraphs, natural rhythm\n- Bold for narrative pivots only\n\n**DON'T:**\n- Write one-line paragraphs (looks AI-generated)\n- Use \"we stopped chasing X\" unless Nava actually chased it\n- Create arguments that are easy to knock down\n- Explain too much — trust the reader\n\n### Split-Brain Problem (CRITICAL - needs investigation)\n\n- **TUI session**: Has its own context/brain\n- **WebUI session**: Separate brain, doesn't know what TUI is doing\n- **WhatsApp (\"Dawn\")**: Can only read memory, has no idea what TUI is currently doing\n- **Suspected cause**: Per-peer session settings vs \"main\" session targeting\n- **Impact**: Cannot check progress remotely via WhatsApp; must use TUI for real-time context\n- **WORKAROUND**: TUI revisions must be saved to shared workspace files so main session can access them\n- **Transcript access**: Raw JSONL at `~/.openclaw/agents/main/sessions/{id}.jsonl` — `sessions_history` API truncates at ~15k bytes; raw file is complete. Read with Python script (see Screenshot Workflow above for pattern).\n\n### Grammarly note: Colored lines in Google Docs = Grammarly, NOT authorial underlining. Do not read as intentional emphasis.\n\n### Draft 001 revision (2026-03-19 evening)\n- Original AI draft: structured, bullet-heavy, vacancy/turnover/compliance framework\n- Tiny's revision: prose narrative, \"what if\" scenario opening, agency perspective, Nava pivot, flowing paragraphs\n- Tiny's version is closer to his voice — narrative > structured list\n- Key features: compressed sentences, bold-for-pivots, first-person naturalism, no bullet lists in post body\n\n### Tiny's LinkedIn Writing Style Rules (formalized 2026-03-20)\n\n**These are the canonical rules for any Nava content. They override default AI writing behavior.**\n\n**Paragraph structure:**\n- No 1-line paragraphs — cluster related ideas into flowing paragraphs\n- Short sentences are fine, but connect them with transitions (\"For\", \"But\", \"Regardless\", \"And\")\n- The AI wrote bullet fragments; prose flows\n\n**Bold usage:**\n- Bold = narrative pivot points, NOT section labels or tags\n- AI used bold as \"Administratively:\" — wrong\n- Tiny uses bold for dramatic emphasis where the story turns\n\n**Argument structure:**\n- Acknowledge the other side's valid arguments BEFORE dismantling them\n- \"Agencies have a fair argument\" — fair first, then complications\n- No strawmen — don't set up easy targets only to knock them down\n\n**Grounded claims:**\n- Never say \"we tried X\" or \"we stopped chasing Y\" unless it actually happened\n- If a hypothetical isn't real, say so explicitly (\"Nice dream. But impractical.\")\n- \"Nice dream, but impractical\" = preferred idiom for killing a hypothetical\n- Never generate action that didn't occur\n\n**Dashes:** No em-dashes (—) or en-dashes (–). Use periods, commas, or separate sentences instead.\n\n**Word repetition:** Don't reuse the same word multiple times in close proximity. If \"different\" appears three times in a paragraph, it's a sign the sentence needs restructuring. Read aloud — ears catch what eyes miss.\n\n**Language register:**\n- No corporate slogans or filler phrases\n- \"Nice dream. But impractical.\" — preferred idiom for killing a hypothetical (not \"we stopped chasing X\")\n- Compressed sentences over long-winded explanations\n- Closer should land clean, not promotional\n- No \"pipe dream\" language in closers — kills the hypothetical then immediately echoes it\n\n**Post vs Image priority:**\n- Post-first when the hook is the copy itself\n- Image-first when the visual metaphor carries the weight\n- Don't default to image search — wait for the user's decision\n\n**Grammarly:**\n- Colored underlines = Grammarly tool artifact, NOT intentional author emphasis\n- Never read underlines as deliberate writing choices\n\n**Critical for agent training:** These rules represent Tiny's distinct voice. They should be encoded into the Nava agent's system prompt as hard constraints, not suggestions. When in doubt, apply these over general LinkedIn best practices.\n- Wants pushback over agreeability during concept development.\n- Strong preference for concept pressure-testing before drafting.\n- LinkedIn workflow preference: concept discussion -> decide image-first/post-first -> finalize LinkedIn post -> derive X -> optional channels.\n- Visual preference: realistic, striking images; caption must complement image (not restate it).\n- Writing style preference: operator/executive tone, compressed sentences, natural short-paragraph rhythm, bullets for real failure cascades, occasional bold pivots (not rigid).\n- Content safety preference: reject off-domain Nava ideas; enforce staffing/recruiting-only taxonomy with source-backed claims.\n- Channel preference: Nava LinkedIn + X mandatory; FB/Yosef/Tiny optional by fit.\n- Visual workflow preference: image concepts must be refined iteratively (multiple directions + critique + refinement), not one-shot generation.\n- User authored Nava blog articles and wants ongoing article-topic suggestions from corpus gaps; ingest/index must refresh with every new article.\n- User wants Google Docs integration for draft critique and style transfer calibration toward their writing voice (alongside existing Gemini custom Gem workflow).\n- X workflow preference: AI can lead first draft (1-3 tweets), user reviews for impact.\n- Primary current project: Nava cross-platform content system and post roadmap execution.\n- Potential channel confusion noted: user suspects duplicate/imposter Dawn on WhatsApp; verify source session/channel before assuming delivery route.\n- Switched to Ollama cloud models (Minimax/Nemotron) after OpenAI tokens ran out (2026-03-19).\n- Primary model: `gemma3:27b-cloud` (just added, in testing)\n- Fallbacks: `minimax-m2.7:cloud` → `minimax-m2.5:cloud` → `nemotron-3-super:cloud`\n- Config backup saved to TinyBackUp before change.\n- Model-routing preference (2026-03-18): default to local Windows Ollama models for routine/structured workflow tasks; escalate to ChatGPT selectively for hard reasoning and high-stakes final polish, with proactive warning before high-token GPT steps.\n- Change-control preference (2026-03-18): before mutating config (especially model routing/gateway behavior), provide read-only diagnosis first and ask for explicit approval; do not make silent config edits.\n- Confidential test phrase to verify split-brain memory sharing (2026-03-17): \"Tiny is in trouble with Betsho because of late payments!\"\n\n---\n\n*Updated: 2026-03-19*\n\n## Screenshot Workflow (2026-03-19)\n\n**Windows screenshots folder (WSL path):**\n`/mnt/c/Users/Tiny4Lurv/OneDrive/Pictures/Screenshots 1/`\n\nAlways `ls -lt` the folder to find the latest file — don't rely on memory for filenames.\n\n**Gemma vision workflow:**\n```python\npython3 - <<'PY'\nimport base64, json, urllib.request\nimg_path = \"/mnt/c/Users/Tiny4Lurv/OneDrive/Pictures/Screenshots 1/Screenshot 2026-03-19 233725.png\"\nwith open(img_path, \"rb\") as f:\n    img_b64 = base64.b64encode(f.read()).decode()\npayload = {\"model\": \"gemma3:27b-cloud\", \"messages\":[{\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": \"Describe this image in detail.\", \"images\": [img_b64]}], \"stream\": False}\nreq = urllib.request.Request(\"http://localhost:11434/api/chat\", data=json.dumps(payload).encode(), headers={\"Content-Type\": \"application/json\"}, method=\"POST\")\nwith urllib.request.urlopen(req, timeout=60) as r:\n    print(json.loads(r.read())[\"message\"][\"content\"])\nPY\n```\n\n## Token Limit Issue (2026-03-19)\n\n- **Problem**: Context limit errors with Ollama cloud models\n- Config has `contextWindow: 204800` for minimax-m2.5:cloud, but API rejects prompts exceeding actual model limits\n- Session hit \"prompt too long; exceeded max context length by 142-228 tokens\"\n- **Fix**: Lower contextWindow in config (recommend 128000 or lower) to prevent overflow errors\n\n---\n\n## Browser Relay Setup (2026-03-19)\n\n### Architecture\n- **chrome-extension** folder: Chrome extension to install in your Windows Chrome\n- **Relay server**: Runs in WSL gateway on port 18792\n- **Connection**: Windows Chrome extension → connects to WSL relay (port 18792) → Gateway controls it\n\n### Fix for \"Profile not found\" errors\n1. **Never set defaultProfile in config** — it breaks the relay\n2. **To use chrome-relay**: always pass `--browser-profile chrome-relay`\n3. **If errors occur**: Check `openclaw browser profiles` — if you see profiles but get errors, restart gateway\n\n### Working command\n```bash\nopenclaw browser --browser-profile chrome-relay screenshot\nopenclaw browser --browser-profile chrome-relay navigate <url>\n```\n\n### Current config state (working)\n- `defaultProfile`: REMOVED (key fix)\n- `profiles.openclaw`: port 18800 (WSL Chrome, not used)\n- `relayBindHost`: 0.0.0.0 (allows external connections)\n\n### Backup files\n- ~/TinyBackUp/20260319/openclaw.json.154346 — current working config\n- ~/TinyBackUp/20260319/MEMORY.md.154348 — current memory\n\n## Nava LinkedIn Posts (2026-03-19)\n\nFound 3 published posts on company page (Aug-Oct 2025):\n- **Oct 3, 2025**: \"The ROI of Investing in Employee Wellness: Why Companies Are Putting Health First\" — 111 reactions, 9 comments\n- **Sep 5, 2025**: \"The Real Cost of Employee Turnover: Why Retention is the New Recruitment\" — 52 reactions, 4 comments\n- **Aug 8, 2025**: \"The Employee Benefit Your Workforce Actually Wants\" — 42 reactions, 4 comments\n\nAdmin URL: https://www.linkedin.com/company/67170741/admin/page-posts/published/\n\n### LinkedIn Page IDs\n- Nava Healthcare (company): 67170741 (not the same as nava-healthcare slug)\n\n### Recent LinkedIn Posts Content (from 2025-03)\n\n**5 days ago - \"The False Finish Line\"**\n- Topic: Most healthcare recruiting teams think the race is over the moment the offer is accepted. In reality, that's a false finish line.\n- Key message: Stay engaged with candidate between offer acceptance and Day 60\n- Nava differentiator: No upfront costs, fees only when confident in placement\n\n**2 weeks ago (Edited) - \"The Universal License Fallacy\"**\n- Topic: A clinical license is a measure of minimum competency, not a predictor of professional success\n- Key message: Don't hire the CV, hire the person behind the qualifications\n- Key concept: Cultural concordance - understanding pace of unit, temperament of leadership, patient demographics\n- Differentiation: Humans with compassionate focus, not AI sifting through CVs\n\n**3 weeks ago - \"The 90-Day Waiting Period\"**\n- Topic: 90-day healthcare benefits waiting period universally hated by clinical candidates\n- Key message: For elite talent (1%), justify strategic exception to drop the red tape\n- Story: A talented DON turned down an offer due to 90-day waiting period; Nava got it reduced to 30 days\n\n**~2 weeks ago - \"The Cost of Vacancies\"**\n- Topic: Break down of the \"backfill spiral\" - what a single vacancy costs a facility\n- Key metrics: Up to $X/day for RN vacancy, 50%+ labor cost inflation from overtime/agency\n\n**~2 weeks ago - \"The Brand Gap\"**\n- Topic: It takes 6 months/millions to approve hospital rebranding, 6 minutes to destroy it\n- Key concept: Employer Brand = leading indicator of Patient Brand\n- Message: Marketing makes the promise, clinical culture delivers it\n\n**Earlier posts (Aug-Oct 2025)** - See full text captured separately\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774000671080}}
