{"type":"message","id":"4a66eae0","parentId":"3ad55086","timestamp":"2026-03-20T09:58:37.229Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"**FOUND THE CULPRIT! 🎯**\n\nLook at the session keys from the API:\n\n```\nagent:main:tui-3dfdda13-4774-41c4-8862-2bdc8ccd1202  ← current\nagent:main:tui-82d0a693-a64c-4580-bfaf-d04cfa4aa8b2  ← previous\nagent:main:tui-5dbda592-e8fa-499c-880d-214bb03f35cf  ← earlier\nagent:main:tui-59d91968-ef9d-484c-be71-fcd3d844de8f  ← ...\nagent:main:tui-7988c1eb-ab4e-4a79-b415-eb420ab0f76a\nagent:main:tui-809165a4-f22b-4bc3-aeba-085a2e2bcf9f\nagent:main:tui-caf1d81b-645f-4e54-b853-6d156ad7e439\nagent:main:tui-b554d0aa-c7c4-4d39-b83a-109dfc13645d\n```\n\n---\n\n## SUSPECT 2 CONFIRMED: Per-peer session creation\n\n**What's happening:**\n- Each TUI connection creates a NEW session with a unique `tui-<uuid>` suffix\n- They're all under the same agent (`main`) but have **different session keys**\n- There's NO `agent:main:main` session for your TUI use (only exists for heartbeat)\n\n**The bug:**\nAccording to the docs, DMs should collapse to `agent:main:main`. But TUI is creating isolated sessions instead.\n\n**Suspects in the chain:**\n1. **TUI client** —，可能是每次连接时传递了新的 peer ID\n2. **Session key generation** — routing可能没有正确处理TUI连接\n3. **dmScope config** — 虽然设为\"main\"，但TUI没有正确使用它\n\nWant me to check the OpenClaw docs or TUI configuration for how to force it to use `agent:main:main`?"}],"stopReason":"stop","api":"ollama","provider":"ollama","model":"minimax-m2.5:cloud","usage":{"input":39575,"output":910,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":40485,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"timestamp":1774000717228}}
