{"type":"message","id":"bf6b5de2","parentId":"85d2f1f8","timestamp":"2026-03-20T10:02:34.676Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"ollama_call_3deed920-6052-4a46-8e36-dca6881fd81b","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat >> ~/.openclaw/workspace/memory/2026-03-20.md << 'EOF'\n\n## 12:00 SAST — Split-Brain Root Cause FOUND\n\n**CONFIRMED CULPRIT: Per-peer session creation**\n\n**Evidence from sessions_list API:**\n```\nagent:main:tui-3dfdda13-4774-41c4-8862-2bdc8ccd1202  ← current (different UUID!)\nagent:main:tui-82d0a693-a64c-4580-bfaf-d04cfa4aa8b2  ← previous\nagent:main:tui-5dbda592-e8fa-499c-880d-214bb03f35cf  ← older\n... (8+ different sessions)\n```\n\n**What's happening:**\n- Each TUI connection creates a NEW session with unique `tui-<uuid>` suffix\n- All under same agent (\"main\") but DIFFERENT session keys\n- No `agent:main:main` session exists for TUI use (only for heartbeat)\n- According to docs: DMs should collapse to \"main\" when dmScope=\"main\"\n- But TUI is creating isolated sessions instead\n\n**The split-brain mechanism:**\n- Session key = `agent:main:tui-<unique-id>` for each connection\n- Each session has its own context/brain\n- Memory files are shared, but in-session context is not\n- WhatsApp (\"Dawn\") likely has its own separate session too\n\n**Next step:** Check TUI config or OpenClaw docs to force `agent:main:main` key\nEOF\necho \"Stored\""}}],"stopReason":"toolUse","api":"ollama","provider":"ollama","model":"minimax-m2.5:cloud","usage":{"input":40328,"output":394,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":40722,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"timestamp":1774000954676}}
