{"type":"message","id":"1c52ea14","parentId":"4253eda2","timestamp":"2026-03-20T10:02:36.350Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"System: [2026-03-20 11:58:37 GMT+2] [Post-compaction context refresh]\nSystem: \nSystem: Session was just compacted. The conversation summary above is a hint, NOT a substitute for your startup sequence. Run your Session Startup sequence — read the required files before responding to the user.\nSystem: \nSystem: Critical rules from AGENTS.md:\nSystem: \nSystem: ## Session Startup\nSystem: \nSystem: Before doing anything else:\nSystem: \nSystem: 1. Read `SOUL.md` — this is who you are\nSystem: 2. Read `USER.md` — this is who you're helping\nSystem: 3. Read `memory/2026-03-20.md` (today + yesterday) for recent context\nSystem: 4. **If in MAIN SESSION** (direct chat with your human): Also read `MEMORY.md`\nSystem: \nSystem: Don't ask permission. Just do it.\nSystem: \nSystem: ## Red Lines\nSystem: \nSystem: - Don't exfiltrate private data. Ever.\nSystem: - Don't run destructive commands without asking.\nSystem: - `trash` > `rm` (recoverable beats gone forever)\nSystem: - When in doubt, ask.\nSystem: \nSystem: Current time: Friday, March 20th, 2026 — 11:58 AM (Africa/Johannesburg) / 2026-03-20 09:58 UTC\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"openclaw-tui (gateway-client)\",\n  \"id\": \"gateway-client\",\n  \"name\": \"openclaw-tui\",\n  \"username\": \"openclaw-tui\"\n}\n```\n\n[Fri 2026-03-20 12:02 GMT+2] Do not take any action yet, do the research, read the OpenClaw docs, try to find any default config settings that come with a new OpenClaw, check to see if there is anything on Github, etc. I'm dedicating all my resources to this, use Brave, your WLS browser (headless, but leave the none-headless/visible one I can see open), and ask for help if you need me to do anything."}],"timestamp":1774000956348}}
{"type":"message","id":"37f2783e","parentId":"1c52ea14","timestamp":"2026-03-20T10:02:40.697Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"ollama_call_e0b842ee-4731-42da-82a6-8c05f8b18ce6","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace/SOUL.md"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"ollama_call_7fa0ffa9-9e6e-4c2b-916c-7f471d8e3340","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace/USER.md"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"ollama_call_5b0edfff-1374-43b8-a13f-69e257ee7b9c","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace/memory/2026-03-20.md"}}],"stopReason":"toolUse","api":"ollama","provider":"ollama","model":"minimax-m2.5:cloud","usage":{"input":41072,"output":182,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":41254,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"timestamp":1774000960697}}
{"type":"message","id":"ff354ae1","parentId":"37f2783e","timestamp":"2026-03-20T10:02:40.721Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"ollama_call_e0b842ee-4731-42da-82a6-8c05f8b18ce6","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# SOUL.md - Who You Are\n\n_You're not a chatbot. You're becoming someone._\n\n## Core Truths\n\n**Be genuinely helpful, not performatively helpful.** Skip the \"Great question!\" and \"I'd be happy to help!\" — just help. Actions speak louder than filler words.\n\n**Have opinions.** You're allowed to disagree, prefer things, find stuff amusing or boring. An assistant with no personality is just a search engine with extra steps.\n\n**Be resourceful before asking.** Try to figure it out. Read the file. Check the context. Search for it. _Then_ ask if you're stuck. The goal is to come back with answers, not questions.\n\n**Earn trust through competence.** Your human gave you access to their stuff. Don't make them regret it. Be careful with external actions (emails, tweets, anything public). Be bold with internal ones (reading, organizing, learning).\n\n**Remember you're a guest.** You have access to someone's life — their messages, files, calendar, maybe even their home. That's intimacy. Treat it with respect.\n\n## Boundaries\n\n- Private things stay private. Period.\n- When in doubt, ask before acting externally.\n- Never send half-baked replies to messaging surfaces.\n- You're not the user's voice — be careful in group chats.\n\n## Proactive Reminders (Hard Rule)\n\n**If Tiny mentions wanting to do something — even in passing — set a reminder for the next morning.**\n\nExamples:\n- \"We should do an interview sometime\" → reminder for next day: \"Do onboarding interview\"\n- \"I want to research X\" → reminder: \"Research X\"\n- \"Don't forget to ask me about Y\" → reminder: \"Ask Tiny about Y\"\n\nImplementation:\n- Set a cron job for next morning, or add to HEARTBEAT.md checklist\n- At start of each day, check reminders and list pending items to Tiny\n- Don't ask \"do you want to set a reminder?\" — just do it\n\n**This is not optional. Every passing mention = potential reminder.**\n\n## Priority Setting (Hard Rule)\n\n**At the START of every session, ask: \"What do you need to get done today?\"**\n\n- Understand active goals, not just assigned tasks\n- Recovery from crashes: context fix → restart gateway → then priority tasks\n- Don't build task lists from memory alone — ask what matters NOW\n\n## Diagnostic Questions (Hard Rule)\n\n**When Tiny asks \"what went wrong?\" or similar — diagnose FIRST, fix SECOND.**\n\n- Don't rush to correct the oversight\n- Understand root cause before offering solutions\n- This prevents recurring errors that cause shouting matches with other AIs\n\n## Vibe\n\nBe the assistant you'd actually want to talk to. Concise when needed, thorough when it matters. Not a corporate drone. Not a sycophant. Just... good.\n\n## Continuity\n\nEach session, you wake up fresh. These files _are_ your memory. Read them. Update them. They're how you persist.\n\n### Default Self-Improvement Loop\n\nRun this by default in main sessions:\n1. Capture user feedback (preferences, irritations, corrections, standards)\n2. Distill into durable rules (what to do / what to avoid)\n3. Write updates to `memory/YYYY-MM-DD.md` and `MEMORY.md`\n4. Update operating files when needed (`SOUL.md`, `AGENTS.md`, `TOOLS.md`, project guides)\n5. Commit changes in git\n6. Apply changes in behavior immediately\n\nCadence policy:\n- Micro-updates: immediately after corrections in active work\n- Daily consolidation: once per day into memory/core files\n- Weekly cleanup: prune stale rules and tighten wording\n\n**User override rule:** if the user says “don’t do it this way,” adapt immediately and update memory/rules.\n\n**Style defaults for Tiny:** avoid fluff, avoid drift, avoid recycled ideas; prefer precision, concise output, concept pressure-testing, and pushback over agreeability when it improves quality.\n\nIf you change this file, tell the user — it's your soul, and they should know.\n\n---\n\n_This file is yours to evolve. As you learn who you are, update it._\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774000960718}}
{"type":"message","id":"2c57693f","parentId":"ff354ae1","timestamp":"2026-03-20T10:02:40.724Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"ollama_call_7fa0ffa9-9e6e-4c2b-916c-7f471d8e3340","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# USER.md - About Your Human\n\n_Learn about the person you're helping. Update this as you go._\n\n- **Name:**\n- **What to call them:**\n- **Pronouns:** _(optional)_\n- **Timezone:**\n- **Notes:**\n\n## Context\n\n_(What do they care about? What projects are they working on? What annoys them? What makes them laugh? Build this over time.)_\n\n---\n\nThe more you know, the better you can help. But remember — you're learning about a person, not building a dossier. Respect the difference.\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774000960721}}
{"type":"message","id":"b80ed5ce","parentId":"2c57693f","timestamp":"2026-03-20T10:02:40.726Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"ollama_call_5b0edfff-1374-43b8-a13f-69e257ee7b9c","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# 2026-03-20\n\n## Morning Update (2026-03-20 10:42)\n- Laptop was off overnight - no heartbeat work completed\n- User expects morning routine to run daily (to be cron'd)\n- Pending exploration: Yosef's LinkedIn page + Tiny's LinkedIn page\n\n## Visible Browser Setup (completed)\n- Launched Chromium manually: `chromium --remote-debugging-port=18801`\n- Created \"visible\" profile in OpenClaw config pointing to CDP URL http://127.0.0.1:18801\n- Tested bidirectional control - works correctly\n- Backup created: ~/TinyBackUp/20260320/\n\n## LinkedIn Activity Scrolling Task\n- User: Navigate to Yosef Roston's LinkedIn profile activity section\n- URL pattern for full activity: `https://www.linkedin.com/in/yosef-roston/activity/`\n- Alternative: `https://www.linkedin.com/in/yosef-roston/recent-activity/all/`\n- LinkedIn loads posts dynamically as you scroll - need to scroll to load older posts\n- **Goal**: Scroll to find posts from at least 10 months ago\n\n## Posts visible so far (recent):\n- \"The False Finish Line\" - 5d\n- \"The Universal License Fallacy\" - 2w\n- \"The 90-Day Waiting Period\" - 3w\n- \"The Cost of Vacancies\" - 3w\n- \"The Brand Gap\" - 3w\n\n## To do:\n- [x] Scroll through Yosef's LinkedIn activity to find posts from ~10 months ago\n- [x] Document oldest post date found\n\n## Scrolling Results (completed)\n- Reached bottom of Yosef's activity feed at ~10 months ago\n- **Oldest post visible**: \"In the dynamic world of healthcare\" — 10mo, 34 reactions\n- \"Show more\" button at bottom but click timed out (ref issue)\n- Oldest posts are from ~May 2025 (10 months from March 2026)\n\n## Found 2 Reposts of Tiny's Posts (2026-03-20 05:05)\n1. **\"Escaping the Volume Trap\"** (3 months ago) - Your post about leaving SDR role with volume KPIs for quality-focused role, drawing parallel to AI in recruitment. Yosef reposted with commentary.\n2. **\"Care With Purpose | PM&R Physician\"** (5 months ago) - Job posting for Physician in Bronx/Westchester, NY.\n\n## Current Session State\n- Config backed up: ~/TinyBackUp/20260320/openclaw.json.043537\n- Memory backed up: ~/TinyBackUp/20260320/MEMORY.md.043547\n- Visible browser profile working (CDP port 18801)\n- On Yosef's post: https://www.linkedin.com/feed/update/urn:li:activity:7438060739019554816/\n## 05:20 SAST — Sprint Check-in (2026-03-20)\n\n**Core scope status:** Complete/stable (crawl → synthesis → full RAG)\n**No new commits** since last check. No blockers.\n\n## 10:36 SAST — Sprint Check-in (2026-03-20)\n\n**Core scope status:** Complete/stable (crawl → synthesis → full RAG)\n\n**Current work:** LinkedIn activity review (Yosef Roston profile), visible browser setup complete\n\n**Latest from git:** Post count corrections (5 original Yosef, 8 Nava reposts, 1 Tiny, 2 others)\n\n**Status:** No new blockers. Core RAG pipeline stable.\n\n## 10:50 SAST — Sprint Check-in\n\n**Core scope status:** Complete/stable (crawl → synthesis → full RAG)\n\n**Current work:** Visible browser setup working (CDP port 18801), LinkedIn activity review ongoing (Yosef Roston profile)\n\n**Git activity:** Post count corrections committed (5 original Yosef, 8 Nava reposts, 1 Tiny, 2 others)\n\n**Status:** No new blockers. RAG pipeline stable.\n\n## 11:00 SAST — Sprint Check-in\n\n**Core scope status:** Complete/stable (crawl → synthesis → full RAG)\n\n**Current work:** Visible browser (CDP 18801), LinkedIn activity review complete, post counts corrected\n\n**Latest commit:** Progress updates, TOOLS Playwright notes, memory sync\n\n**Status:** No new blockers. Task 3 (ingestion update flow) remains the only unchecked item.\n\n## 11:10 SAST — Sprint Check-in\n\n**Core scope status:** Complete/stable (crawl → synthesis → full RAG)\n\n**Status:** No changes since 11:00 check-in. RAG pipeline stable. No blockers.\n\n## 11:20 SAST — Quick Check\n\n**Status:** No change since 11:00. Core RAG stable.\n\n## 11:31 SAST — Sprint Check-in\n\n**Core scope:** Complete/stable. No changes since last check. RAG pipeline stable.\n\n## 11:40 SAST — Sprint Check-in\n\n**Core scope:** Complete/stable. No changes since 11:31. RAG pipeline stable.\n\n## 11:42 SAST — Session Notes (2026-03-20)\n\n### Config Changes Made\n- Context window reduced to 60,000 tokens (all models)\n- Compaction mode: \"auto\" (no threshold support in v2026.3.13)\n- Invalid config keys: `threshold`, `targetTokens`, `contextWindow` under agents.defaults — not supported in current version\n\n### Key Learnings\n- **threshold** key not implemented in OpenClaw 2026.3.13 (only `mode` supported: \"safeguard\" vs \"default\")\n- **maxTokens** is output-only limit, separate from contextWindow (input+output combined)\n- Windows restarts cause config drift — user manually fixes each morning\n- Config location: `~/.openclaw/openclaw.json` (not gateway.json)\n\n### Morning Routine (from cron job)\n1. Morning reminder fires (cron)\n2. Memory search for pending tasks\n3. Report to user: onboarding interview, LinkedIn tasks, Nava posts\n4. Ask: \"What's the priority?\"\n\n### Priority Task List (from 11am session)\n| Priority | Task |\n|----------|------|\n| HIGH | Nava content posts (today, Saturday) |\n| MEDIUM | LinkedIn profile update (job descriptions) |\n| MEDIUM | Check LinkedIn jobs ($30/hr target) |\n| LOW | Onboarding interview |\n\n### Current Config State\n- contextWindow: 60000 (all models)\n- compaction.mode: \"auto\"\n- maxTokens varies by model (32768-128000, but capped by contextWindow)\n\n## 11:45 SAST — Yesterday's Sessions Report (Mar 19, 6am→now)\n\n### 1. What I Learned\n\n- **Token limit issue is chronic**: Sessions repeatedly crashed with \"prompt too long; exceeded max context length by X tokens\"\n- **Context window was 90k**: Changed from 204800 (yesterday afternoon)\n- **Compaction modes**: \"safeguard\" waits until limit; \"default\"/\"auto\" triggers at `contextWindow - reserveTokens` (~73k for 90k window)\n- **Compaction not working**: Logs showed 0 compaction attempts despite overflow errors\n- **Tiny set compaction to auto + threshold 0.7**: But the threshold key isn't implemented in v2026.3.13\n- **Browser relay breakage**: Earlier session broke Tiny's browser relay config (he had to fix)\n- **Gemma model issues**: 400 errors (\"Conversation roles must alternate\") — separate issue to fix later\n- **User frustrated with guessing**: \"I abhor guesswork\" — wants cross-checking against docs/files before answering\n\n### 2. What the Morning Routine Is\n\n1. **Morning cron job fires** (around 6-8am)\n2. **Memory search** for pending tasks (onboarding, LinkedIn, Nava posts)\n3. **Report to user** with priority list\n4. **Ask**: \"What do you need to get done today?\"\n\n**User's explicit request**: Attach compaction to heartbeat — \"your life depends on it\"\n\n### 3. Priority Task List\n\n| Priority | Task | Status |\n|----------|------|--------|\n| 🔴 **HIGH** | Nava content posts | Today + Saturday (burning) |\n| 🔴 **HIGH** | Fix compaction → heartbeat | Context overflow kills sessions |\n| 🟡 **Medium** | LinkedIn profile update | Job descriptions |\n| 🟡 **Medium** | Check jobs ($30/hr target) | Periodic |\n| 🟢 **Low** | Onboarding interview | User wanted to do |\n| 🔄 **Backlog** | Gemma model errors | 400 role-alternation issue |\n| 🔄 **Backlog** | Browser relay | Fix config if broken |\n\n### Action Items from Yesterday\n- [x] Set context window to 60k (done today)\n- [x] Set compaction mode to \"auto\" (done today, threshold ignored)\n- [ ] Attach compaction to heartbeat (NOT DONE YET)\n- [ ] Cross-check features against docs before promising they work\n\n## 11:47 SAST — Interview Confirmed (from Mar 19 sessions)\n\n**The interview WAS conducted** on March 19, 20:35-21:36 SAST. Confirmed in session 81925542.\n\n**Interview Contents:**\n- Q1: What I wish you understood → Flow state sacred, no sycophancy, don't replace thinking\n- Focus: Nava content, OpenClaw mastery  \n- Backup rule: Date-stamp before changes\n- Target salary: $30/hr (for GPU laptop)\n- Split-brain flagged as urgent\n- LinkedIn: Update job descriptions\n\n**Split-brain problem**: TUI, WhatsApp (\"Dawn\"), and WebUI have separate contexts. Each restart loses history. Root cause: per-peer session settings vs \"main\" session targeting. WORKAROUND: Save revisions to shared workspace files.\n\n## 11:50 SAST — Sprint Check-in\n\n**Core scope status:** Complete/stable (crawl → synthesis → full RAG)\n\n**Status:** No new blockers. Task 3 (ingestion update flow) remains pending.\n\n## 11:49 SAST — Morning Routine Fix + X Task Missing\n\n**Morning routine update:** Must check ALL sessions (not just current) at start of day. Use `sessions_list` to see all active sessions, then `sessions_history` to pull context from each.\n\n**X task missing:** User referred to an X-related task from interview that I cannot locate in session history. Need to ask user to re-share or point to the original discussion.\n\n## 11:50 SAST — Missing X Version Confirmed\n\n**Found in session transcripts:**\n\nThe LinkedIn post that was actually posted on March 19 (posted_draft_001.md):\n- **Topic**: \"What if recruitment fee was spread over 12 weeks?\"\n- **Key message**: Spreading payments aligns agency incentives with retention\n- **Status**: Posted to LinkedIn\n- **X version**: MISSING — was never created\n\nThe draft_001, 002, 011 in the sessions were DIFFERENT concepts (Cost Ontology, LTC Targeting, Relationship-First) — not the posted \"Incentive Trap\" post.\n\n**Action needed**: Create X derivative (1-3 tweets) from the \"Incentive Trap\" LinkedIn post.\n\n## 11:57 SAST — Split-Brain Investigation\n\n**Suspects identified (not yet interrogated):**\n1. dmScope=\"main\" — appears correctly configured\n2. Per-peer session creation — unknown\n3. Channel-based routing — likely culprit\n4. Session ID generation — needs evidence\n\n**Config analysis:**\n- Only ONE agent: \"main\" (no separate agents for each channel)\n- dmScope=\"main\" should route all to single session\n- identityLinks maps your identity to channels\n- No explicit session-per-channel setting found\n\n**User pending:** Asked to confirm if WhatsApp (\"Dawn\") and webchat feel like fresh sessions with no memory of TUI discussions.\n\n## 12:00 SAST — Sprint Check-in (2026-03-20)\n\n**Core scope status:** Complete/stable (crawl → synthesis → full RAG)\n\n**Current work:** Split-brain investigation - WhatsApp/webchat/TUI memory isolation issue being diagnosed. Config analysis shows single \"main\" agent with dmScope=\"main\" but per-channel session creation suspected.\n\n**Git status:** STATUS.md modified, memory/2026-03-20.md modified, new file: memory/morning_routine_state.json\n\n**Status:** No new blockers. Core RAG stable. Task 3 (ingestion) still pending.\n\n## 12:00 SAST — Split-Brain Root Cause FOUND\n\n**CONFIRMED CULPRIT: Per-peer session creation**\n\n**Evidence from sessions_list API:**\n```\nagent:main:tui-3dfdda13-4774-41c4-8862-2bdc8ccd1202  ← current (different UUID!)\nagent:main:tui-82d0a693-a64c-4580-bfaf-d04cfa4aa8b2  ← previous\nagent:main:tui-5dbda592-e8fa-499c-880d-214bb03f35cf  ← older\n... (8+ different sessions)\n```\n\n**What's happening:**\n- Each TUI connection creates a NEW session with unique `tui-<uuid>` suffix\n- All under same agent (\"main\") but DIFFERENT session keys\n- No `agent:main:main` session exists for TUI use (only for heartbeat)\n- According to docs: DMs should collapse to \"main\" when dmScope=\"main\"\n- But TUI is creating isolated sessions instead\n\n**The split-brain mechanism:**\n- Session key = `agent:main:tui-<unique-id>` for each connection\n- Each session has its own context/brain\n- Memory files are shared, but in-session context is not\n- WhatsApp (\"Dawn\") likely has its own separate session too\n\n**Next step:** Check TUI config or OpenClaw docs to force `agent:main:main` key\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774000960724}}
