{"type":"message","id":"49d73be0","parentId":"98f1ca7e","timestamp":"2026-03-20T10:02:44.919Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"ollama_call_893bf518-aba4-4105-8cdf-7ae38b94b20f","toolName":"web_search","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"query\": \"OpenClaw tui session key agent:main:main configuration\",\n  \"provider\": \"brave\",\n  \"count\": 10,\n  \"tookMs\": 1472,\n  \"externalContent\": {\n    \"untrusted\": true,\n    \"source\": \"web_search\",\n    \"provider\": \"brave\",\n    \"wrapped\": true\n  },\n  \"results\": [\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"854b7c0ee3d7f5f4\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nTUI - OpenClaw\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"854b7c0ee3d7f5f4\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://docs.openclaw.ai/web/tui\",\n      \"description\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"afd49f653eaca235\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nSession keys are stored as agent:&lt;agentId&gt;:&lt;sessionKey&gt;. <strong>If you type /session main, the TUI expands it to agent:&lt;currentAgent&gt;:main</strong>.\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"afd49f653eaca235\\\">>>\",\n      \"siteName\": \"docs.openclaw.ai\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"32ef2bd751bd6868\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nFeature: --agent flag for TUI to select which agent handles the session · Issue #8892 · openclaw/openclaw\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"32ef2bd751bd6868\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://github.com/openclaw/openclaw/issues/8892\",\n      \"description\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"3d4565c77d94a1e7\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nSummary When running openclaw tui, there&#x27;s currently no way to directly connect to a specific agent defined in agents.list. <strong>The --session flag only sets the session key/name, but the conversation is still handled by agent main</strong>. Current B...\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"3d4565c77d94a1e7\\\">>>\",\n      \"published\": \"February 4, 2026\",\n      \"siteName\": \"github.com\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"c312017af2715b3f\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nTUI | Docs | OpenClaw\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"c312017af2715b3f\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://openclaws.io/docs/web/tui/\",\n      \"description\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"a6fb655e2fc76574\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nSession keys are stored as agent:&lt;agentId&gt;:&lt;sessionKey&gt;. <strong>If you type /session main, the TUI expands it to agent:&lt;currentAgent&gt;:main</strong>.\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"a6fb655e2fc76574\\\">>>\",\n      \"siteName\": \"openclaws.io\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"bea71b9d607ec0fc\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nOpenClaw Tutorial: From Localhost to Agentic AI (Safely)\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"bea71b9d607ec0fc\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://productos-ai.com/en/blog/openclaw-tutorial-setup-security-guide\",\n      \"description\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"5a6292cc15ac8094\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nThe TUI will launch. Do not try to be a hero and choose &quot;Advanced&quot; yet. Select QuickStart (Spacebar to select, Enter to confirm). Select Provider: Choose Anthropic. Paste API Key: Copy it from your dashboard. ⚠️ Security Note: This key is stored locally in ~/.openclaw/config.json.\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"5a6292cc15ac8094\\\">>>\",\n      \"siteName\": \"productos-ai.com\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"9a660e9712a4f63c\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nGitHub - openclawq/clawmonitor: help you monitor OpenClaw Agents/Sessions. GitHub\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"9a660e9712a4f63c\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://github.com/openclawq/clawmonitor/\",\n      \"description\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"99ad2d7ce78b3863\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nclawmonitor snapshot --format json clawmonitor snapshot --format md clawmonitor nudge --session-key &#x27;agent:main:main&#x27; --template progress clawmonitor nudge --session-key &#x27;agent:main:main&#x27; --template continue clawmonitor push --session-key &#x27;agent:main:main&#x27; --dry-run clawmonitor status clawmonitor status --detail clawmonitor status --format json clawmonitor status --format md clawmonitor status --format md --detail clawmonitor cron clawmonitor models clawmonitor models --mode direct --format json clawmonitor models --mode openclaw --timeout 15 clawmonitor tree clawmonitor report --session-key &#x27;agent:main:main&#x27; --format both clawmonitor watch --interval 1\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"99ad2d7ce78b3863\\\">>>\",\n      \"siteName\": \"github.com\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"58085bbd44b87f05\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nSession Management - OpenClaw Documentation\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"58085bbd44b87f05\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://open-claw.blog/docs/session.html\",\n      \"description\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"06d9b59e685aaf32\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nOpenClaw treats one direct-chat session per agent as primary. <strong>Direct chats collapse to agent:&lt;agentId&gt;:&lt;mainKey&gt; (default main),</strong> while group/channel chats get their own keys. session.mainKey is honored.\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"06d9b59e685aaf32\\\">>>\",\n      \"siteName\": \"open-claw.blog\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"d63ecc90cd837e4c\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nRun OpenClaw in two commands on WSL2/Ubuntu | by AlexHe99 | Feb, 2026 | Medium\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"d63ecc90cd837e4c\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://medium.com/@alexhe.amd/run-openclaw-in-two-commands-on-wsl2-ubuntu-75717a1c3174\",\n      \"description\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"4871c06800a43dfd\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\n│ ◆ Model/auth provider │ ... new configuration by run openclaw tui . openclaw tui - <strong>ws://127.0.0.1:18789 - agent main - session main session agent:main:main</strong> hello Hey....\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"4871c06800a43dfd\\\">>>\",\n      \"published\": \"February 3, 2026\",\n      \"siteName\": \"medium.com\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"346824afa1348455\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\n[Bug]: --to flag ignored when using --agent with custom channel, all sessions map to main · Issue #41483 · openclaw/openclaw\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"346824afa1348455\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://github.com/openclaw/openclaw/issues/41483\",\n      \"description\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"085369b7e8397cc7\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nCheck sessions: cat ~/.openclaw/agents/chatwoot_agent/sessions/sessions.json · Each unique --to value should create a separate session with a unique sessionKey, e.g. agent:chatwoot_agent:cw_111 and agent:chatwoot_agent:cw_222 · Both calls share the same session: agent:chatwoot_agent:main The --to flag is completely ignored for session routing.\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"085369b7e8397cc7\\\">>>\",\n      \"published\": \"1 week ago\",\n      \"siteName\": \"github.com\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"b7769bc6fd56ec50\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nTUI: add --agent flag to openclaw tui · Issue #19247 · openclaw/openclaw\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"b7769bc6fd56ec50\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://github.com/openclaw/openclaw/issues/19247\",\n      \"description\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"2d813c40d17effd5\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nYou switched accounts on another tab or window. Reload to refresh your session. ... There was an error while loading. Please reload this page. ... <strong>openclaw tui always routes to the default (main) agent</strong>.\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"2d813c40d17effd5\\\">>>\",\n      \"published\": \"1 month ago\",\n      \"siteName\": \"github.com\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"3f6e7e21714501e2\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\n2026 Complete Guide: OpenClaw ACP - Bridge Your IDE to AI Agents - DEV Community\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"3f6e7e21714501e2\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://dev.to/czmilo/2026-complete-guide-openclaw-acp-bridge-your-ide-to-ai-agents-3hl8\",\n      \"description\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"de03e28a7ef17b09\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nThis means: ... # Connect to main agent session <strong>openclaw acp --session agent:main:main</strong> # Connect to design agent openclaw acp --session agent:design:main # Connect to a specific bug fix session openclaw acp --session agent:qa:bug-123\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"de03e28a7ef17b09\\\">>>\",\n      \"published\": \"2 weeks ago\",\n      \"siteName\": \"dev.to\"\n    }\n  ]\n}"}],"details":{"query":"OpenClaw tui session key agent:main:main configuration","provider":"brave","count":10,"tookMs":1472,"externalContent":{"untrusted":true,"source":"web_search","provider":"brave","wrapped":true},"results":[{"title":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"854b7c0ee3d7f5f4\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nTUI - OpenClaw\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"854b7c0ee3d7f5f4\">>>","url":"https://docs.openclaw.ai/web/tui","description":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"afd49f653eaca235\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nSession keys are stored as agent:&lt;agentId&gt;:&lt;sessionKey&gt;. <strong>If you type /session main, the TUI expands it to agent:&lt;currentAgent&gt;:main</strong>.\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"afd49f653eaca235\">>>","siteName":"docs.openclaw.ai"},{"title":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"32ef2bd751bd6868\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nFeature: --agent flag for TUI to select which agent handles the session · Issue #8892 · openclaw/openclaw\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"32ef2bd751bd6868\">>>","url":"https://github.com/openclaw/openclaw/issues/8892","description":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"3d4565c77d94a1e7\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nSummary When running openclaw tui, there&#x27;s currently no way to directly connect to a specific agent defined in agents.list. <strong>The --session flag only sets the session key/name, but the conversation is still handled by agent main</strong>. Current B...\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"3d4565c77d94a1e7\">>>","published":"February 4, 2026","siteName":"github.com"},{"title":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"c312017af2715b3f\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nTUI | Docs | OpenClaw\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"c312017af2715b3f\">>>","url":"https://openclaws.io/docs/web/tui/","description":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"a6fb655e2fc76574\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nSession keys are stored as agent:&lt;agentId&gt;:&lt;sessionKey&gt;. <strong>If you type /session main, the TUI expands it to agent:&lt;currentAgent&gt;:main</strong>.\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"a6fb655e2fc76574\">>>","siteName":"openclaws.io"},{"title":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"bea71b9d607ec0fc\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nOpenClaw Tutorial: From Localhost to Agentic AI (Safely)\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"bea71b9d607ec0fc\">>>","url":"https://productos-ai.com/en/blog/openclaw-tutorial-setup-security-guide","description":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"5a6292cc15ac8094\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nThe TUI will launch. Do not try to be a hero and choose &quot;Advanced&quot; yet. Select QuickStart (Spacebar to select, Enter to confirm). Select Provider: Choose Anthropic. Paste API Key: Copy it from your dashboard. ⚠️ Security Note: This key is stored locally in ~/.openclaw/config.json.\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"5a6292cc15ac8094\">>>","siteName":"productos-ai.com"},{"title":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"9a660e9712a4f63c\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nGitHub - openclawq/clawmonitor: help you monitor OpenClaw Agents/Sessions. GitHub\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"9a660e9712a4f63c\">>>","url":"https://github.com/openclawq/clawmonitor/","description":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"99ad2d7ce78b3863\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nclawmonitor snapshot --format json clawmonitor snapshot --format md clawmonitor nudge --session-key &#x27;agent:main:main&#x27; --template progress clawmonitor nudge --session-key &#x27;agent:main:main&#x27; --template continue clawmonitor push --session-key &#x27;agent:main:main&#x27; --dry-run clawmonitor status clawmonitor status --detail clawmonitor status --format json clawmonitor status --format md clawmonitor status --format md --detail clawmonitor cron clawmonitor models clawmonitor models --mode direct --format json clawmonitor models --mode openclaw --timeout 15 clawmonitor tree clawmonitor report --session-key &#x27;agent:main:main&#x27; --format both clawmonitor watch --interval 1\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"99ad2d7ce78b3863\">>>","siteName":"github.com"},{"title":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"58085bbd44b87f05\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nSession Management - OpenClaw Documentation\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"58085bbd44b87f05\">>>","url":"https://open-claw.blog/docs/session.html","description":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"06d9b59e685aaf32\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nOpenClaw treats one direct-chat session per agent as primary. <strong>Direct chats collapse to agent:&lt;agentId&gt;:&lt;mainKey&gt; (default main),</strong> while group/channel chats get their own keys. session.mainKey is honored.\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"06d9b59e685aaf32\">>>","siteName":"open-claw.blog"},{"title":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"d63ecc90cd837e4c\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nRun OpenClaw in two commands on WSL2/Ubuntu | by AlexHe99 | Feb, 2026 | Medium\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"d63ecc90cd837e4c\">>>","url":"https://medium.com/@alexhe.amd/run-openclaw-in-two-commands-on-wsl2-ubuntu-75717a1c3174","description":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"4871c06800a43dfd\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\n│ ◆ Model/auth provider │ ... new configuration by run openclaw tui . openclaw tui - <strong>ws://127.0.0.1:18789 - agent main - session main session agent:main:main</strong> hello Hey....\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"4871c06800a43dfd\">>>","published":"February 3, 2026","siteName":"medium.com"},{"title":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"346824afa1348455\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\n[Bug]: --to flag ignored when using --agent with custom channel, all sessions map to main · Issue #41483 · openclaw/openclaw\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"346824afa1348455\">>>","url":"https://github.com/openclaw/openclaw/issues/41483","description":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"085369b7e8397cc7\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nCheck sessions: cat ~/.openclaw/agents/chatwoot_agent/sessions/sessions.json · Each unique --to value should create a separate session with a unique sessionKey, e.g. agent:chatwoot_agent:cw_111 and agent:chatwoot_agent:cw_222 · Both calls share the same session: agent:chatwoot_agent:main The --to flag is completely ignored for session routing.\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"085369b7e8397cc7\">>>","published":"1 week ago","siteName":"github.com"},{"title":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"b7769bc6fd56ec50\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nTUI: add --agent flag to openclaw tui · Issue #19247 · openclaw/openclaw\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"b7769bc6fd56ec50\">>>","url":"https://github.c