earch\\n---\\n[Bug] /session command doesn't create session until first message sent · Issue #5931 · openclaw/openclaw\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"6c47af4e8c6e9fa7\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://github.com/openclaw/openclaw/issues/5931\",\n      \"description\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"54976ce0cb5dc877\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\n// In setSession (tui-session-actions.js or webchat equivalent) await client.patchSession({ key: nextKey });\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"54976ce0cb5dc877\\\">>>\",\n      \"published\": \"February 1, 2026\",\n      \"siteName\": \"github.com\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"838e991f523116b1\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nControl UI: session picker + “New chat” (new sessionKey) + rename (avoid everything being `agent:main:main`) · Issue #29563 · openclaw/openclaw\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"838e991f523116b1\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://github.com/openclaw/openclaw/issues/29563\",\n      \"description\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"63f0bd487a856163\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nVersion: OpenClaw 2026.2.26 (bc50708), Gateway Control UI (web) Problem: In Control UI, direct chat typically stays on the same sessionKey (often agent:main:main). Using /new resets/archives the transcript (new sessionId) but does NOT create a new sessionKey.\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"63f0bd487a856163\\\">>>\",\n      \"published\": \"3 weeks ago\",\n      \"siteName\": \"github.com\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"b44f15db4ed3d970\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nHow to Set Up OpenClaw: Your 24/7 AI Agent, Step by Step\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"b44f15db4ed3d970\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://mrprompts.substack.com/p/how-to-set-up-openclaw-your-247-ai\",\n      \"description\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"cb94bd7242991940\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nThis isn’t a limitation. Clean instructions produce clean output every single time, regardless of what happened in previous sessions. ... Pause here. Two well-configured agents will surprise you with how much they handle before you ever need a third. OpenClaw has real system access.\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"cb94bd7242991940\\\">>>\",\n      \"published\": \"1 month ago\",\n      \"siteName\": \"mrprompts.substack.com\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"1a20e7dbef861e3d\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\n2026 Complete Guide: OpenClaw ACP - Bridge Your IDE to AI Agents - DEV Community\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"1a20e7dbef861e3d\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://dev.to/czmilo/2026-complete-guide-openclaw-acp-bridge-your-ide-to-ai-agents-3hl8\",\n      \"description\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"6ec8b39e5c7f5366\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nThe OpenClaw ACP bridge speaks ACP over stdio (standard input/output), making it compatible with any IDE or tooling that supports the protocol. It forwards prompts to the OpenClaw Gateway over WebSocket and maintains session mappings, so your AI conversations persist across editor restarts.\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"6ec8b39e5c7f5366\\\">>>\",\n      \"published\": \"2 weeks ago\",\n      \"siteName\": \"dev.to\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"a54670088ad18460\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nrun openclaw tui on that session and see what its outputting, im guess a connection timeout or somet - Friends of the Crustacean 🦞🤝\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"a54670088ad18460\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://www.answeroverflow.com/m/1468716144268541985?focus=1468716144268541985\",\n      \"description\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"f1a553fa466c2ebd\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nAgent failed before reply: No API key found for provider &quot;anthropic&quot;. Auth store: /srv/clawdbot/state/agents/main/agent/auth-profiles.json (agentDir: /srv/clawdbot/state/agents/main/agent). Configure auth for this agent (clawdbot agents add &lt;id&gt;) or copy auth-profiles.json from the main agentDir.\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"f1a553fa466c2ebd\\\">>>\",\n      \"published\": \"February 4, 2026\",\n      \"siteName\": \"www.answeroverflow.com\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"d41eb4e06e131ce6\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nacp | Claw\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"d41eb4e06e131ce6\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://docs.claw.so/engine/cli/acp/\",\n      \"description\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"15ad30a19c39cfd4\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nOne agent can have many sessions; ACP defaults to an isolated acp:&lt;uuid&gt; session unless you override the key or label. Add a custom ACP agent in ~/.config/zed/settings.json (or use Zed’s Settings UI): ... In Zed, open the Agent panel and select “OpenClaw ACP” to start a thread.\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"15ad30a19c39cfd4\\\">>>\",\n      \"siteName\": \"docs.claw.so\"\n    }\n  ]\n}"}],"details":{"query":"OpenClaw default session key tui client each connection new session","provider":"brave","count":10,"tookMs":1430,"externalContent":{"untrusted":true,"source":"web_search","provider":"brave","wrapped":true},"results":[{"title":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"9848f70168ea0a22\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nTUI - OpenClaw\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"9848f70168ea0a22\">>>","url":"https://docs.openclaw.ai/web/tui","description":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"88f55d673bfaae59\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nFooter: connection state + agent + session + model + think/fast/verbose/reasoning + token counts + deliver. Input: text editor with autocomplete. Agents are unique slugs (e.g. main, research). The Gateway exp