{"type":"message","id":"0f918da5","parentId":"2524a13f","timestamp":"2026-03-20T10:03:28.563Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"ollama_call_dd81c26c-95df-41f0-9096-b2d798af7adb","toolName":"web_search","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"query\": \"OpenClaw source code tui session key new session each connect\",\n  \"provider\": \"brave\",\n  \"count\": 10,\n  \"tookMs\": 1430,\n  \"externalContent\": {\n    \"untrusted\": true,\n    \"source\": \"web_search\",\n    \"provider\": \"brave\",\n    \"wrapped\": true\n  },\n  \"results\": [\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"e79355188c7db0b4\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nTUI - OpenClaw\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"e79355188c7db0b4\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://docs.openclaw.ai/web/tui\",\n      \"description\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"f1e427384e72c125\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nFooter: connection state + agent + session + model + think/fast/verbose/reasoning + token counts + deliver. Input: text editor with autocomplete. Agents are unique slugs (e.g. main, research). The Gateway exposes the list. Sessions belong to the current agent. Session keys are stored as agent:&lt;agentId&gt;:&lt;sessionKey&gt;. If you type /session main, the TUI expands it to agent:&lt;currentAgent&gt;:main.\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"f1e427384e72c125\\\">>>\",\n      \"siteName\": \"docs.openclaw.ai\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"7cb276961a0f73db\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nFeature: --agent flag for TUI to select which agent handles the session · Issue #8892 · openclaw/openclaw\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"7cb276961a0f73db\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://github.com/openclaw/openclaw/issues/8892\",\n      \"description\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"6677397e71f87b5b\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nSummary When running openclaw tui, there&#x27;s currently no way to directly connect to a specific agent defined in agents.list. <strong>The --session flag only sets the session key/name</strong>, but the conversation is still handled by agent main. Current B...\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"6677397e71f87b5b\\\">>>\",\n      \"published\": \"February 4, 2026\",\n      \"siteName\": \"github.com\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"493b6acb27e7afc9\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nSession Management - OpenClaw Documentation\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"493b6acb27e7afc9\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://open-claw.blog/docs/session.html\",\n      \"description\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"c7cf4d0e1adb8aed\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nOpenClaw treats one direct-chat session per agent as primary. Direct chats collapse to agent:&lt;agentId&gt;:&lt;mainKey&gt; (default main), while group/channel chats get their own keys. session.mainKey is honored.\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"c7cf4d0e1adb8aed\\\">>>\",\n      \"siteName\": \"open-claw.blog\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"fd33eba084d915b6\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nTUI | Docs | OpenClaw\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"fd33eba084d915b6\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://openclaws.io/docs/web/tui/\",\n      \"description\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"c78ddc4dc2625c39\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nFooter: connection state + agent + session + model + think/fast/verbose/reasoning + token counts + deliver. Input: text editor with autocomplete. Agents are unique slugs (e.g. main, research). The Gateway exposes the list. Sessions belong to the current agent. Session keys are stored as agent:&lt;agentId&gt;:&lt;sessionKey&gt;. If you type /session main, the TUI expands it to agent:&lt;currentAgent&gt;:main.\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"c78ddc4dc2625c39\\\">>>\",\n      \"siteName\": \"openclaws.io\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"9d2586088012f204\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nOpenclaw - Your Code, Your AI, Your Rules\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"9d2586088012f204\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://openclaw.im/docs/concepts/session\",\n      \"description\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"82cbd159d636e389\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nMultiple phone numbers and channels can map to the same agent main key; they act as transports into one conversation. ... per-account-channel-peer: agent:&lt;agentId&gt;:&lt;channel&gt;:&lt;accountId&gt;:dm:&lt;peerId&gt; (accountId defaults to default). If session.identityLinks matches a provider-prefixed peer id (for example telegram:123), the canonical key replaces &lt;peerId&gt; so the same person shares a session across channels.\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"82cbd159d636e389\\\">>>\",\n      \"siteName\": \"openclaw.im\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"36eee4c56e0f804f\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nOpenClaw\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"36eee4c56e0f804f\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://github.com/openclaw/openclaw/compare/openclaw:f6e5b67...openclaw:61d171a.diff\",\n      \"description\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"53fb7ccaaf32e25b\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nTUI/session-key alias event matching: treat chat events whose session keys are canonical aliases (for example agent: :main vs main) as the same session while preserving cross-agent isolation, so assistant replies no longer disappear or surface in another terminal window due to strict key-form mismatch. (#33937) Thanks @yjh1412. - OpenAI Codex OAuth/login parity: keep openclaw ...\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"53fb7ccaaf32e25b\\\">>>\",\n      \"siteName\": \"github.com\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"fbef0a8322b22e2e\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\n[Bug] /session command doesn't create session until first message sent · Issue #5931 · openclaw/openclaw\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"fbef0a8322b22e2e\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://github.com/openclaw/openclaw/issues/5931\",\n      \"description\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"30c06f2e341f0745\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\n// <strong>In setSession (tui-session-actions.js or webchat equivalent) await client.patchSession({ key: nextKey });</strong>\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"30c06f2e341f0745\\\">>>\",\n      \"published\": \"February 1, 2026\",\n      \"siteName\": \"github.com\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"52233915c13762f8\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nOpenClaw Tutorial: From Localhost to Agentic AI (Safely)\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"52233915c13762f8\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://productos-ai.com/en/blog/openclaw-tutorial-setup-security-guide\",\n      \"description\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"582a335a84e575fe\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nPaste this token into the OpenClaw TUI when prompted. Once the TUI says &quot;Gateway Connected,&quot; send a &quot;Hello&quot; to your new bot on Telegram. If it replies, you are live. Most devs treat this like ChatGPT—a stateless session.\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"582a335a84e575fe\\\">>>\",\n      \"siteName\": \"productos-ai.com\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"0c879a8b073936cb\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nSession Management | openclaw/openclaw | DeepWiki\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"0c879a8b073936cb\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://deepwiki.com/openclaw/openclaw/2.4-session-management\",\n      \"description\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"2f18cd9ae41bfde7\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nThis document describes OpenClaw&#x27;s session management system: how conversations are identified, isolated, persisted, and synchronized across the Gateway and Agent execution layers. Sessions maintain c\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"2f18cd9ae41bfde7\\\">>>\",\n      \"published\": \"1 week ago\",\n      \"siteName\": \"deepwiki.com\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"75fca00b48909daa\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nrun openclaw tui on that session and see what its outputting, im guess a connection timeout or somet - Friends of the Crustacean 🦞🤝\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"75fca00b48909daa\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://www.answeroverflow.com/m/1468716144268541985?focus=1468716144268541985\",\n      \"description\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"b819ecab73937858\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nrun openclaw tui on that session and see what its outputting, im guess a connection timeout or something\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"b819ecab73937858\\\">>>\",\n      \"published\": \"February 4, 2026\",\n      \"siteName\": \"www.answeroverflow.com\"\n    }\n  ]\n}"}],"details":{"query":"OpenClaw source code tui session key new session each connect","provider":"brave","count":10,"tookMs":1430,"externalContent":{"untrusted":true,"source":"web_search","provider":"brave","wrapped":true},"results":[{"title":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"e79355188c7db0b4\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nTUI - OpenClaw\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"e79355188c7db0b4\">>>","url":"https://docs.openclaw.ai/web/tui","description":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"f1e427384e72c125\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nFooter: connection state + agent + session + model + think/fast/verbose/reasoning + token counts + deliver. Input: text editor with autocomplete. Agents are unique slugs (e.g. main, research). The Gateway exposes the list. Sessions belong to the current agent. Session keys are stored as agent:&lt;agentId&gt;:&lt;sessionKey&gt;. If you type /session main, the TUI expands it to agent:&lt;currentAgent&gt;:main.\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"f1e427384e72c125\">>>","siteName":"docs.openclaw.ai"},{"title":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"7cb276961a0f73db\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nFeature: --agent flag for TUI to select which agent handles the session · Issue #8892 · openclaw/openclaw\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"7cb276961a0f73db\">>>","url":"https://github.com/openclaw/openclaw/issues/8892","description":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"6677397e71f87b5b\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nSummary When running openclaw tui, there&#x27;s currently no way to directly connect to a specific agent defined in agents.list. <strong>The --session flag only sets the session key/name</strong>, but the conversation is still handled by agent main. Current B...\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"6677397e71f87b5b\">>>","published":"February 4, 2026","siteName":"github.com"},{"title":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"493b6acb27e7afc9\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nSession Management - OpenClaw Documentation\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"493b6acb27e7afc9\">>>","url":"https://open-claw.blog/docs/session.html","description":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"c7cf4d0e1adb8aed\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nOpenClaw treats one direct-chat session per agent as primary. Direct chats collapse to agent:&lt;agentId&gt;:&lt;mainKey&gt; (default main), while group/channel chats get their own keys. session.mainKey is honored.\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"c7cf4d0e1adb8aed\">>>","siteName":"open-claw.blog"},{"title":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"fd33eba084d915b6\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nTUI | Docs | OpenClaw\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"fd33eba084d915b6\">>>","url":"https://openclaws.io/docs/web/tui/","description":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"c78ddc4dc2625c39\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nFooter: connection state + agent + session + model + think/fast/verbose/reasoning + token counts + deliver. Input: text editor with autocomplete. Agents are unique slugs (e.g. main, research). The Gateway exposes the list. Sessions belong to the current agent. Session keys are stored as agent:&lt;agentId&gt;:&lt;sessionKey&gt;. If you type /session main, the TUI expands it to agent:&lt;currentAgent&gt;:main.\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"c78ddc4dc2625c39\">>>","siteName":"openclaws.io"},{"title":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"9d2586088012f204\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nOpenclaw - Your Code, Your AI, Your Rules\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"9d2586088012f204\">>>","url":"https://openclaw.im/docs/concepts/session","description":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"82cbd159d636e389\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nMultiple phone numbers and channels can map to the same agent main key; they act as transports into one conversation. ... per-account-channel-peer: agent:&lt;agentId&gt;:&lt;channel&gt;:&lt;accountId&gt;:dm:&lt;peerId&gt; (accountId defaults to default). If session.identityLinks matches a provider-prefixed peer id (for example telegram:123), the canonical key replaces &lt;peerId&gt; so the same person shares a session across channels.\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"82cbd159d636e389\">>>","siteName":"openclaw.im"},{"title":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"36eee4c56e0f804f\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nOpenClaw\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"36eee4c56e0f804f\">>>","url":"https://github.com/openclaw/openclaw/compare/openclaw:f6e5b67...openclaw:61d171a.diff","description":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"53fb7ccaaf32e25b\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nTUI/session-key alias event matching: treat chat events whose session keys are canonical aliases (for example agent: :main vs main) as the same session while preserving cross-agent isolation, so assistant replies no longer disappear or surface in another terminal window due to strict key-form mismatch. (#33937) Thanks @yjh1412. - OpenAI Codex OAuth/login parity: keep openclaw ...\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"53fb7ccaaf32e25b\">>>","siteName":"github.com"},{"title":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"fbef0a8322b22e2e\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\n[Bug] /session command doesn't create session until first message sent · Issue #5931 · openclaw/openclaw\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"fbef0a8322b22e2e\">>>","url":"https://github.com/openclaw/openclaw/issues/5931","description":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"30c06f2e341f0745\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\n// <strong>In setSession (tui-session-actions.js or webchat equivalent) await client.patchSession({ key: nextKey });</strong>\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"30c06f2e341f0745\">>>","published":"February 1, 2026","siteName":"github.com"},{"title":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"52233915c13762f8\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nOpenClaw Tutorial: From Localhost to Agentic AI (Safely)\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"52233915c13762f8\">>>","url":"https://productos-ai.com/en/blog/openclaw-tutorial-setup-security-guide","description":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"582a335a84e575fe\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nPaste this token into the OpenClaw TUI when prompted. Once the TUI says &quot;Gateway Connected,&quot; send a &quot;Hello&quot; to your new bot on Telegram. If it replies, you are live. Most devs treat this like ChatGPT—a stateless session.\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"582a335a84e575fe\">>>","siteName":"productos-ai.com"},{"title":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"0c879a8b073936cb\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nSession Management | openclaw/openclaw | DeepWiki\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"0c879a8b073936cb\">>>","url":"https://deepwiki.com/openclaw/openclaw/2.4-session-management","description":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"2f18cd9ae41bfde7\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nThis document describes OpenClaw&#x27;s session management system: how conversations are identified, isolated, persisted, and synchronized across the Gateway and Agent execution layers. Sessions maintain c\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"2f18cd9ae41bfde7\">>>","published":"1 week ago","siteName":"deepwiki.com"},{"title":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"75fca00b48909daa\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nrun openclaw tui on that session and see what its outputting, im guess a connection timeout or somet - Friends of the Crustacean 🦞🤝\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"75fca00b48909daa\">>>","url":"https://www.answeroverflow.com/m/1468716144268541985?focus=1468716144268541985","description":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"b819ecab73937858\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nrun openclaw tui on that session and see what its outputting, im guess a connection timeout or something\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"b819ecab73937858\">>>","published":"February 4, 2026","siteName":"www.answeroverflow.com"}]},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774001008560}}
