{"type":"message","id":"3c861a3f","parentId":"1bd5acde","timestamp":"2026-03-20T10:03:36.598Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"ollama_call_da650c61-62b6-4d00-8389-c715f147db87","toolName":"web_search","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"query\": \"OpenClaw tui default session key \\\"main\\\" auto generate client\",\n  \"provider\": \"brave\",\n  \"count\": 10,\n  \"tookMs\": 1325,\n  \"externalContent\": {\n    \"untrusted\": true,\n    \"source\": \"web_search\",\n    \"provider\": \"brave\",\n    \"wrapped\": true\n  },\n  \"results\": [\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"14e3d158458fcbc2\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\ntui - OpenClaw\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"14e3d158458fcbc2\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://docs.openclaw.ai/cli/tui\",\n      \"description\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"16a020f2680a964e\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\n<strong>When launched from inside a configured agent workspace directory, TUI auto-selects that agent for the session key default</strong> (unless --session is explicitly agent:&lt;id&gt;:...). ... openclaw tui openclaw tui --url ws://127.0.0.1:18789 --token &lt;token&gt; ...\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"16a020f2680a964e\\\">>>\",\n      \"siteName\": \"docs.openclaw.ai\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"21bd9edcb77fdf9f\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nSession Management - OpenClaw Documentation\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"21bd9edcb77fdf9f\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://open-claw.blog/docs/session.html\",\n      \"description\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"03e28ebe0c620446\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nOpenClaw treats one direct-chat session per agent as primary. Direct chats collapse to agent:<strong>&lt;agentId&gt;:&lt;mainKey&gt; (default main),</strong> while group/channel chats get their own keys. session.mainKey is honored.\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"03e28ebe0c620446\\\">>>\",\n      \"siteName\": \"open-claw.blog\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"b9a4a3c91b9cd4ce\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nFeature: --agent flag for TUI to select which agent handles the session · Issue #8892 · openclaw/openclaw\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"b9a4a3c91b9cd4ce\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://github.com/openclaw/openclaw/issues/8892\",\n      \"description\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"f8745afd533bf4d6\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nSummary When running openclaw tui, there&#x27;s currently no way to directly connect to a specific agent defined in agents.list. The --session flag only sets the session key/name, but the conversation is still handled by agent main. Current B...\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"f8745afd533bf4d6\\\">>>\",\n      \"published\": \"February 4, 2026\",\n      \"siteName\": \"github.com\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"d6f7aaa570ea6613\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nfeat: designate a channel session as the primary/main session · Issue #40017 · openclaw/openclaw\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"d6f7aaa570ea6613\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://github.com/openclaw/openclaw/issues/40017\",\n      \"description\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"75a9f3d70f52230b\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nopenclaw config set agents.defaults.mainSession &quot;agent:main:slack:direct:u0agh2wkbjp&quot; # or openclaw sessions set-primary &lt;session-key&gt;\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"75a9f3d70f52230b\\\">>>\",\n      \"published\": \"2 weeks ago\",\n      \"siteName\": \"github.com\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"d187670aa48f533d\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nRun OpenClaw in two commands on WSL2/Ubuntu | by AlexHe99 | Feb, 2026 | Medium\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"d187670aa48f533d\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://medium.com/@alexhe.amd/run-openclaw-in-two-commands-on-wsl2-ubuntu-75717a1c3174\",\n      \"description\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"4a68677d4a3cbdfe\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\n◇ What now ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────╮ │ │ │ What now: https://clawd.bot/showcase (&quot;What People Are Building&quot;). │ │ │ ├──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────╯ │ └ Onboarding complete. Use the tokenized dashboard link above to control Clawdbot. clawdbot tui - ws://127.0.0.1:18789 - agent main - session main session agent:main:main Wake up, my friend!\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"4a68677d4a3cbdfe\\\">>>\",\n      \"published\": \"February 3, 2026\",\n      \"siteName\": \"medium.com\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"c5878e08949efb08\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nWebchat TUI: 'Session file path must be within ...\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"c5878e08949efb08\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://github.com/openclaw/openclaw/issues/15883\",\n      \"description\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"ac950bd7543d4384\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nIn paths-*.js, resolvePathWithinSessionsDir() resolves the session transcript path against a sessionsDir that appears to default to the main/default agent&#x27;s sessions directory (~/.openclaw/agents/main/sessions/), even when the session belongs to a different agent (~/.openclaw/agents/stellar/sessions/). The relative path then contains ../stellar/... which fails the security check: if (relative.startsWith(&#x27;..&#x27;) || path.isAbsolute(relative)) throw new Error(&#x27;Session file path must be within sessions directory&#x27;); The webchat TUI should resolve session transcript paths using the correct agent&#x27;s sessions directory based on the agent ID in the session key.\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"ac950bd7543d4384\\\">>>\",\n      \"published\": \"February 14, 2026\",\n      \"siteName\": \"github.com\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"594341d7f27c5b7e\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\n2026 Complete Guide: OpenClaw ACP - Bridge Your IDE to AI Agents - DEV Community\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"594341d7f27c5b7e\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://dev.to/czmilo/2026-complete-guide-openclaw-acp-bridge-your-ide-to-ai-agents-3hl8\",\n      \"description\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"3c9f51966ce53d9c\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nThe OpenClaw ACP bridge speaks ACP over stdio (standard input/output), making it compatible with any IDE or tooling that supports the protocol. It forwards prompts to the OpenClaw Gateway over WebSocket and maintains session mappings, so your AI conversations persist across editor restarts.\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"3c9f51966ce53d9c\\\">>>\",\n      \"published\": \"2 weeks ago\",\n      \"siteName\": \"dev.to\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"f86c0a2d7a1be9f3\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nrun openclaw tui on that session and see what its outputting, im guess a connection timeout or somet - Friends of the Crustacean 🦞🤝\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"f86c0a2d7a1be9f3\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://www.answeroverflow.com/m/1468716144268541985?focus=1468716144268541985\",\n      \"description\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"9ddd20cc6381be5f\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nAgent failed before reply: No API key found for provider &quot;anthropic&quot;. Auth store: /srv/clawdbot/state/agents/main/agent/auth-profiles.json (agentDir: /srv/clawdbot/state/agents/main/agent). Configure auth for this agent (clawdbot agents add &lt;id&gt;) or copy auth-profiles.json from the main agentDir.\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"9ddd20cc6381be5f\\\">>>\",\n      \"published\": \"February 4, 2026\",\n      \"siteName\": \"www.answeroverflow.com\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"bc5591e5636478f1\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nSession Management | openclaw/openclaw | DeepWiki\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"bc5591e5636478f1\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://deepwiki.com/openclaw/openclaw/2.4-session-management\",\n      \"description\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"36800724f2bf4023\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nThis document describes OpenClaw&#x27;s session management system: how conversations are identified, isolated, persisted, and synchronized across the Gateway and Agent execution layers. Sessions maintain c\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"36800724f2bf4023\\\">>>\",\n      \"published\": \"1 week ago\",\n      \"siteName\": \"deepwiki.com\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"fd9498f0affc22fb\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nopenclaw/CHANGELOG.md at main · openclaw/openclaw\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"fd9498f0affc22fb\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://github.com/openclaw/openclaw/blob/main/CHANGELOG.md\",\n      \"description\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"3513a5089c6998bd\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nDocker/timezone override: add OPENCLAW_TZ so docker-setup.sh can pin gateway and CLI containers to a chosen IANA timezone instead of inheriting the daemon default. (#34119) Thanks @Lanfei. Dependencies/pi: bump @mariozechner/pi-agent-core, @mariozechner/pi-ai, @mariozechner/pi-coding-agent, and @mariozechner/pi-tui to 0.58.0. Cron/sessions: add sessionTarget: &quot;current&quot; and session:&lt;id&gt; support so cron jobs can bind to the creating session or a persistent named session instead of only main or isolated.\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"3513a5089c6998bd\\\">>>\",\n      \"siteName\": \"github.com\"\n    }\n  ]\n}"}],"details":{"query":"OpenClaw tui default session key \"main\" auto generate client","provider":"brave","count":10,"tookMs":1325,"externalContent":{"untrusted":true,"source":"web_search","provider":"brave","wrapped":true},"results":[{"title":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"14e3d158458fcbc2\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\ntui - OpenClaw\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"14e3d158458fcbc2\">>>","url":"https://docs.openclaw.ai/cli/tui","description":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"16a020f2680a964e\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\n<strong>When launched from inside a configured agent workspace directory, TUI auto-selects that agent for the session key default</strong> (unless --session is explicitly agent:&lt;id&gt;:...). ... openclaw tui openclaw tui --url ws://127.0.0.1:18789 --token &lt;token&gt; ...\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"16a020f2680a964e\">>>","siteName":"docs.openclaw.ai"},{"title":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"21bd9edcb77fdf9f\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nSession Management - OpenClaw Documentation\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"21bd9edcb77fdf9f\">>>","url":"https://open-claw.blog/docs/session.html","description":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"03e28ebe0c620446\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nOpenClaw treats one direct-chat session per agent as primary. Direct chats collapse to agent:<strong>&lt;agentId&gt;:&lt;mainKey&gt; (default main),</strong> while group/channel chats get their own keys. session.mainKey is honored.\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"03e28ebe0c620446\">>>","siteName":"open-claw.blog"},{"title":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"b9a4a3c91b9cd4ce\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nFeature: --agent flag for TUI to select which agent handles the session · Issue #8892 · openclaw/openclaw\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"b9a4a3c91b9cd4ce\">>>","url":"https://github.com/openclaw/openclaw/issues/8892","description":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"f8745afd533bf4d6\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nSummary When running openclaw tui, there&#x27;s currently no way to directly connect to a specific agent defined in agents.list. The --session flag only sets the session key/name, but the conversation is still handled by agent main. Current B...\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"f8745afd533bf4d6\">>>","published":"February 4, 2026","siteName":"github.com"},{"title":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"d6f7aaa570ea6613\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nfeat: designate a channel session as the primary/main session · Issue #40017 · openclaw/openclaw\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"d6f7aaa570ea6613\">>>","url":"https://github.com/openclaw/openclaw/issues/40017","description":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"75a9f3d70f52230b\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nopenclaw config set agents.defaults.mainSession &quot;agent:main:slack:direct:u0agh2wkbjp&quot; # or openclaw sessions set-primary &lt;session-key&gt;\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"75a9f3d70f52230b\">>>","published":"2 weeks ago","siteName":"github.com"},{"title":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"d187670aa48f533d\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nRun OpenClaw in two commands on WSL2/Ubuntu | by AlexHe99 | Feb, 2026 | Medium\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"d187670aa48f533d\">>>","url":"https://medium.com/@alexhe.amd/run-openclaw-in-two-commands-on-wsl2-ubuntu-75717a1c3174","description":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"4a68677d4a3cbdfe\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\n◇ What now ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────╮ │ │ │ What now: https://clawd.bot/showcase (&quot;What People Are Building&quot;). │ │ │ ├──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────╯ │ └ Onboarding complete. Use the tokenized dashboard link above to control Clawdbot. clawdbot tui - ws://127.0.0.1:18789 - agent main - session main session agent:main:main Wake up, my friend!\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"4a68677d4a3cbdfe\">>>","published":"February 3, 2026","siteName":"medium.com"},{"title":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"c5878e08949efb08\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nWebchat TUI: 'Session file path must be within ...\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"c5878e08949efb08\">>>","url":"https://github.com/openclaw/openclaw/issues/15883","description":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"ac950bd7543d4384\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nIn paths-*.js, resolvePathWithinSessionsDir() resolves the session transcript path against a sessionsDir that appears to default to the main/default agent&#x27;s sessions directory (~/.openclaw/agents/main/sessions/), even when the session belongs to a different agent (~/.openclaw/agents/stellar/sessions/). The relative path then contains ../stellar/... which fails the security check: if (relative.startsWith(&#x27;..&#x27;) || path.isAbsolute(relative)) throw new Error(&#x27;Session file path must be within sessions directory&#x27;); The webchat TUI should resolve session transcript paths using the correct agent&#x27;s sessions directory based on the agent ID in the session key.\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"ac950bd7543d4384\">>>","published":"February 14, 2026","siteName":"github.com"},{"title":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"594341d7f27c5b7e\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\n2026 Complete Guide: OpenClaw ACP - Bridge Your IDE to AI Agents - DEV Community\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"594341d7f27c5b7e\">>>","url":"https://dev.to/czmilo/2026-complete-guide-openclaw-acp-bridge-your-ide-to-ai-agents-3hl8","description":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"3c9f51966ce53d9c\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nThe OpenClaw ACP bridge speaks ACP over stdio (standard input/output), making it compatible with any IDE or tooling that supports the protocol. It forwards prompts to the OpenClaw Gateway over WebSocket and maintains session mappings, so your AI conversations persist across editor restarts.\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"3c9f51966ce53d9c\">>>","published":"2 weeks ago","siteName":"dev.to"},{"title":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"f86c0a2d7a1be9f3\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nrun openclaw tui on that session and see what its outputting, im guess a connection timeout or somet - Friends of the Crustacean 🦞🤝\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"f86c0a2d7a1be9f3\">>>","url":"https://www.answeroverflow.com/m/1468716144268541985?focus=1468716144268541985","description":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"9ddd20cc6381be5f\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nAgent failed before reply: No API key found for provider &quot;anthropic&quot;. Auth store: /srv/clawdbot/state/agents/main/agent/auth-profiles.json (agentDir: /srv/clawdbot/state/agents/main/agent). Configure auth for this agent (clawdbot agents add &lt;id&gt;) or copy auth-profiles.json from the main agentDir.\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"9ddd20cc6381be5f\">>>","published":"February 4, 2026","siteName":"www.answeroverflow.com"},{"title":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"bc5591e5636478f1\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nSession Management | openclaw/openclaw | DeepWiki\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"bc5591e5636478f1\">>>","url":"https://deepwiki.com/openclaw/openclaw/2.4-session-management","description":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"36800724f2bf4023\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nThis document describes OpenClaw&#x27;s session management system: how conversations are identified, isolated, persisted, and synchronized across the Gateway and Agent execution layers. Sessions maintain c\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"36800724f2bf4023\">>>","published":"1 week ago","siteName":"deepwiki.com"},{"title":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"fd9498f0affc22fb\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nopenclaw/CHANGELOG.md at main · openclaw/openclaw\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"fd9498f0affc22fb\">>>","url":"https://github.com/openclaw/openclaw/blob/main/CHANGELOG.md","description":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"3513a5089c6998bd\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nDocker/timezone override: add OPENCLAW_TZ so docker-setup.sh can pin gateway and CLI containers to a chosen IANA timezone instead of inheriting the daemon default. (#34119) Thanks @Lanfei. Dependencies/pi: bump @mariozechner/pi-agent-core, @mariozechner/pi-ai, @mariozechner/pi-coding-agent, and @mariozechner/pi-tui to 0.58.0. Cron/sessions: add sessionTarget: &quot;current&quot; and session:&lt;id&gt; support so cron jobs can bind to the creating session or a persistent named session instead of only main or isolated.\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"3513a5089c6998bd\">>>","siteName":"github.com"}]},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774001016596}}
