{"type":"message","id":"47ea9e67","parentId":"4edf2996","timestamp":"2026-03-20T10:04:02.971Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\n\n## 🎯 INVESTIGATION COMPLETE — ROOT CAUSE FOUND\n\n### The Culprit\n**`session.scope` is missing from your config**\n\n- Default value: `\"per-sender\"` — each TUI connection creates a **NEW session** with a unique ID\n- Your sessions are: `agent:main:tui-3dfd...`, `agent:main:tui-82d0...`, etc.\n- Should be: `agent:main:main` (single shared session)\n\n### The Fix\nAdd to `openclaw.json`:\n```json\n\"session\": {\n  \"scope\": \"global\"\n}\n```\n\nThis tells TUI to always use the \"main\" session instead of spawning new ones.\n\n### Why This Happens\nThe TUI defaults to `per-sender` which is designed for multi-user scenarios where each terminal gets its own conversation. But for a single user (you), it creates the split-brain problem.\n\n---\n\n**Ready when you are to implement.**"}],"stopReason":"stop","api":"ollama","provider":"ollama","model":"minimax-m2.5:cloud","usage":{"input":35907,"output":216,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":36123,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"timestamp":1774001042970}}
